name: Bulbasaur
version_x: For some time after its birth, it uses the nutrients that are packed into the seed on its back in order to grow.
version_y: It carries a seed on its back right from birth. As its body grows larger, the seed does too.

name: Ivysaur
version_x: The more sunlight Ivysaur bathes in, the more strength wells up within it, allowing the bud on its back to grow larger.
version_y: The bulb on its back grows as it absorbs nutrients. The bulb gives off a pleasant aroma when it blooms.

name: Venusaur
version_x: While it basks in the sun, it can convert the light into energy. As a result, it is more powerful in the summertime.
version_y: By spreading the broad petals of its flower and catching the sun’s rays, it fills its body with power.

name: Charmander
version_x: The flame on its tail shows the strength of its life-force. If Charmander is weak, the flame also burns weakly.
version_y: If Charmander is healthy, the flame on the tip of its tail will burn vigorously and won’t go out even if it gets a bit wet.

name: Charmeleon
version_x: When it swings its burning tail, the temperature around it rises higher and higher, tormenting its opponents.
version_y: It is very hotheaded by nature, so it constantly seeks opponents to battle against. Its aggression will not be quelled if it doesn’t win.

name: Charizard
version_x: If Charizard becomes truly angered, the flame at the tip of its tail burns in a light blue shade.
version_y: It uses its wings to fly sky-high. The more experience it gains in battle, the greater the temperature at which its flames burn.

name: Squirtle
version_x: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. It sprays a potent foam from its mouth.
version_y: Its shell is soft immediately after it is born. In no time at all, the shell becomes so resilient that a prodding finger will bounce right off it.

name: Wartortle
version_x: Wartortle’s long, furry tail is a symbol of longevity, so this Pokémon is quite popular among older people.
version_y: It often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. While swimming quickly, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

name: Blastoise
version_x: It deliberately increases its body weight so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.
version_y: It has jet nozzles on its shell. This impressive Pokémon uses these jets to charge toward foes with all the force of a rocket.

name: Caterpie
version_x: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.
version_y: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

name: Metapod
version_x: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.
version_y: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can’t withstand a harsh attack.

name: Butterfree
version_x: It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.
version_y: It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

name: Weedle
version_x: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.
version_y: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

name: Kakuna
version_x: Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.
version_y: Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

name: Beedrill
version_x: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.
version_y: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

name: Pidgey
version_x: Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.
version_y: Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

name: Pidgeotto
version_x: This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.
version_y: This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

name: Pidgeot
version_x: This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.
version_y: This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

name: Rattata
version_x: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.
version_y: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

name: Raticate
version_x: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.
version_y: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

name: Spearow
version_x: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.
version_y: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

name: Fearow
version_x: A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.
version_y: A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

name: Ekans
version_x: It can freely detach its jaw to swallow large prey whole. It can become too heavy to move, however.
version_y: A very common sight in grasslands and such. It flicks its tongue in and out to sense danger in its surroundings.

name: Arbok
version_x: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.
version_y: This Pokémon is very tenacious. Once it targets its prey, it won’t give up the chase, no matter how far the prey goes.

name: Pikachu
version_x: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.
version_y: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.

name: Raichu
version_x: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.
version_y: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.

name: Sandshrew
version_x: It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger, it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.
version_y: No matter how high a place it falls from, this Pokémon can save itself by rolling into a ball and bouncing.

name: Sandslash
version_x: It is adept at attacking with the spines on its back and its sharp claws while quickly scurrying about.
version_y: The spikes on its body are made up of its hardened hide. It rolls up and attacks foes with its spikes.

name: Nidoran♀
version_x: Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging, they’ll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.
version_y: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran’s horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male’s horn.

name: Nidorina
version_x: The horn on its head has atrophied. It’s thought that this happens so Nidorina’s children won’t get poked while their mother is feeding them.
version_y: If the group is threatened, these Pokémon will band together to assault enemies with a chorus of ultrasonic waves.

name: Nidoqueen
version_x: Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.
version_y: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

name: Nidoran♂
version_x: The horn on a male Nidoran’s forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.
version_y: Small but brave, this Pokémon will hold its ground and even risk its life in battle to protect the female it’s friendly with.

name: Nidorino
version_x: With a horn that’s harder than diamond, this Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.
version_y: It’s nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

name: Nidoking
version_x: When it goes on a rampage, it’s impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it’s lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.
version_y: Nidoking prides itself on its strength. It’s forceful and spirited in battle, making use of its thick tail and diamond-crushing horn.

name: Clefairy
version_x: On nights with a full moon, Clefairy gather from all over and dance. Bathing in moonlight makes them float.
version_y: On nights with a full moon, they gather together and dance. The surrounding area is enveloped in an abnormal magnetic field.

name: Clefable
version_x: Said to live in quiet, remote mountains, this type of fairy has a strong aversion to being seen.
version_y: It has an acute sense of hearing. It can easily hear a pin being dropped nearly 1,100 yards away.

name: Vulpix
version_x: If it is attacked by an enemy that is stronger than itself, it feigns injury to fool the enemy and escapes.
version_y: As its body grows larger, its six warm tails become more beautiful, with a more luxurious coat of fur.

name: Ninetales
version_x: Some legends claim that each of its nine tails has its own unique type of special mystical power.
version_y: It has nine long tails and fur that gleams gold. It is said to live for 1,000 years.

name: Jigglypuff
version_x: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.
version_y: If it inflates to sing a lullaby, it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.

name: Wigglytuff
version_x: It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.
version_y: The rich, fluffy fur that covers its body feels so good that anyone who feels it can’t stop touching it.

name: Zubat
version_x: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.
version_y: Zubat live in caves, down where the sun’s light won’t reach. In the morning, they gather together to keep each other warm as they sleep.

name: Golbat
version_x: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.
version_y: Its feet are tiny, but this Pokémon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.

name: Oddish
version_x: Its scientific name is Oddium wanderus. It is said to cover distances as far as 1,000 feet when night falls, walking on its two roots.
version_y: When it is woken by moonlight, it wanders about. But during the day, it stays still underground.

name: Gloom
version_x: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn’t drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.
version_y: It secretes a sticky, drool-like nectar. Though sweet, it smells too repulsive to get very close.

name: Vileplume
version_x: The bud bursts into bloom with a bang. It then starts scattering allergenic, poisonous pollen.
version_y: It fiendishly scatters allergenic pollen from its petals, which are the largest in the world.

name: Paras
weakness: Fire, , Ice, Poison, Flying, , Bug, Rock
version_x: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.
version_y: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

name: Parasect
weakness: Fire, , Ice, Poison, Flying, , Bug, Rock
version_x: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.
version_y: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

name: Venonat
version_x: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokémon at night that are attracted by light.
version_y: Its eyes act as radar, enabling it to be active in darkness. The eyes can also shoot powerful beams.

name: Venomoth
version_x: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.
version_y: When it attacks, it flaps its large wings violently to scatter its poisonous powder all around.

name: Diglett
version_x: It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.
version_y: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light, its blood heats up, causing it to grow weak.

name: Dugtrio
version_x: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.
version_y: In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.

name: Meowth
version_x: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.
version_y: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines, too.

name: Persian
version_x: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.
version_y: It has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. This is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.

name: Psyduck
version_x: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.
version_y: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.

name: Golduck
version_x: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.
version_y: It swims gracefully along on the quiet, slow-moving rivers and lakes of which it is so fond.

name: Mankey
version_x: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.
version_y: It is extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next instant.

name: Primeape
version_x: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.
version_y: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poké Ball.

name: Growlithe
version_x: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.
version_y: It’s very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.

name: Arcanine
version_x: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.
version_y: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can’t help but grovel before it.

name: Poliwag
version_x: The swirl on its belly is its insides showing through the skin. It appears more clearly after Poliwag eats.
version_y: Its legs are newly grown, and it can’t walk very well. It seems to prefer swimming through the water instead.

name: Poliwhirl
version_x: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.
version_y: Its skin is moist all over its body. The skin on its belly spiral also feels smooth.

name: Poliwrath
version_x: Although it’s skilled in a style of dynamic swimming that uses all its muscles, for some reason it lives on dry land.
version_y: It can use its well-developed arms and legs to run on the surface of the water for a split second.

name: Abra
version_x: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.
version_y: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

name: Kadabra
version_x: Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.
version_y: This Pokémon’s telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.

name: Alakazam
version_x: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.
version_y: Alakazam wields potent psychic powers. It’s said that this Pokémon used these powers to create the spoons it holds.

name: Machop
version_x: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.
version_y: Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.

name: Machoke
version_x: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.
version_y: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

name: Machamp
version_x: It punches with its four arms at blinding speed. It can launch 1,000 punches in two seconds.
version_y: It can knock a train flying with a punch. However, it is terrible at delicate work using its fingers.

name: Bellsprout
version_x: No matter what Bellsprout is doing, if it detects movement nearby, it will immediately react by reaching out with its thin vines.
version_y: It plants its feet deep underground to rehydrate itself. While doing so, it’s unable to run away if it’s attacked.

name: Weepinbell
version_x: Even though it is filled with acid, it does not melt because it also oozes a protective fluid.
version_y: The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.

name: Victreebel
version_x: It lures prey into its mouth with a nectar-like aroma. The helpless prey is melted with a dissolving fluid.
version_y: After dissolving many prey, this Pokémon’s acid becomes sweeter. This makes it even easier to attract more prey.

name: Tentacool
version_x: When the tide goes out, dehydrated Tentacool can be found left behind on the shore.
version_y: Its eyes are as transparent as crystals. From them, it shoots mysterious beams of light.

name: Tentacruel
version_x: On the rare occasions that large outbreaks of Tentacruel occur, all fish Pokémon disappear from the surrounding sea.
version_y: In battle, it extends all 80 of its tentacles to entrap its opponent inside a poisonous net.

name: Geodude
weakness: Water, , Grass, , Ice, Fighting, Ground, Steel
version_x: At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.
version_y: Most people may not notice, but a closer look should reveal that there are many Geodude around.

name: Graveler
weakness: Water, , Grass, , Ice, Fighting, Ground, Steel
version_x: A slow walker, it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path.
version_y: Moss-covered rocks are Graveler’s favorite food. It consumes over a ton of them a day, crunching loudly while it eats.

name: Golem
weakness: Water, , Grass, , Ice, Fighting, Ground, Steel
version_x: It is enclosed in a hard shell that is as rugged as slabs of rock. It sheds skin once a year to grow larger.
version_y: It deliberately blows itself up, then uses this explosive force to jump from mountain to mountain.

name: Ponyta
version_x: About an hour after birth, Ponyta’s fiery mane and tail grow out, giving the Pokémon an impressive appearance.
version_y: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parents. It runs all day in fields and on mountains.

name: Rapidash
version_x: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.
version_y: It has astounding acceleration. From a standstill, it can reach top speed within 10 steps.

name: Slowpoke
version_x: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.
version_y: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

name: Slowbro
version_x: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.
version_y: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, this Pokémon reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.

name: Magnemite
version_x: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.
version_y: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges electromagnetic waves and so on from the units at its sides.

name: Magneton
version_x: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.
version_y: They’re formed by several Magnemite linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

name: Farfetch’d
version_x: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.
version_y: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

name: Doduo
version_x: Its twin heads have exactly the same genes and battle in perfect sync with each other.
version_y: Its heads never sleep at the same time—each one takes a turn keeping watch while the other sleeps, switching every hour or so.

name: Dodrio
version_x: It now has three hearts and three sets of lungs. Though it can’t run as fast as Doduo, Dodrio can keep running for longer stretches of time.
version_y: The strongest head with the thickest neck becomes the leader and gains primary control of the body.

name: Seel
version_x: The protrusion on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.
version_y: The colder it gets, the better it feels. It joyfully swims around oceans so cold that they are filled with floating ice.

name: Dewgong
version_x: It sleeps under shallow ocean waters during the day, then looks for food at night when it’s colder.
version_y: It stores thermal energy in its body to fend off the cold. It swims at eight knots even in frigid waters.

name: Grimer
version_x: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.
version_y: When two of these Pokémon’s bodies are combined together, new poisons are created.

name: Muk
version_x: It’s thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
version_y: It’s so stinky! Muk’s body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.

name: Shellder
version_x: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.
version_y: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.

name: Cloyster
version_x: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.
version_y: When attacked, it launches its spikes in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

name: Gastly
version_x: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.
version_y: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.

name: Haunter
version_x: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.
version_y: In total darkness, where nothing is visible, Haunter lurks, silently stalking its next victim.

name: Gengar
version_x: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey’s shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.
version_y: Hiding in people’s shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.

name: Onix
weakness: Water, , Grass, , Ice, Fighting, Ground, Steel
version_x: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.
version_y: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.

name: Drowzee
version_x: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children’s are much tastier.
version_y: When it twitches its nose, it can tell where someone is sleeping and what that person is dreaming about.

name: Hypno
version_x: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.
version_y: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.

name: Krabby
version_x: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.
version_y: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

name: Kingler
version_x: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.
version_y: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

name: Voltorb
version_x: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.
version_y: It’s usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.

name: Electrode
version_x: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.
version_y: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of the Bomb Ball.

name: Exeggcute
weakness: Fire, Ice, Poison, Flying, Bug, , Ghost, Dark
version_x: If you touch one of Exeggcute’s heads, mistaking it for an egg, the other heads will quickly gather and attack you in a swarm.
version_y: Using telepathy only fellow Exeggcute can pick up on, they always form a cluster of six.

name: Exeggutor
weakness: Fire, Ice, Poison, Flying, Bug, , Ghost, Dark
version_x: It is called the Walking Jungle. Each of the nuts has a face and a will of its own.
version_y: It is said that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an Exeggcute.

name: Cubone
version_x: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.
version_y: This Pokémon wears the skull of its deceased mother. Sometimes Cubone’s dreams make it cry, but each tear Cubone sheds makes it stronger.

name: Marowak
version_x: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.
version_y: When this Pokémon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak’s temperament also turned vicious at the same time.

name: Hitmonlee
version_x: At the exact moment it lands a kick on its target, Hitmonlee hardens the muscles on the sole of its foot, maximizing the power of the kick.
version_y: It has complete control over the ligaments in its legs, expanding and contracting them to double the reach of its kicks.

name: Hitmonchan
version_x: It corners its foes with combo punches from both sides, then finishes them off with a single straight punch launched at over 300 mph.
version_y: Its fists are masses of muscle. It takes a break every three minutes to steady its breath and mood.

name: Lickitung
version_x: If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won’t go away, either.
version_y: Bug Pokémon are Lickitung’s main food source. This Pokémon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue, then swallows the prey whole.

name: Koffing
version_x: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.
version_y: The poisonous gases it contains are a little bit lighter than air. That’s why it’s always slightly airborne.

name: Weezing
version_x: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.
version_y: When it inhales poisonous gases from garbage, its body expands, and its insides smell much worse.

name: Rhyhorn
weakness: Water, , Grass, , Ice, Fighting, Ground, Steel
version_x: Rhyhorn claims an area with over a six mile radius as its territory. It apparently forgets where this territory is when running, however.
version_y: Once it starts running, it won’t stop—even if it crashes through boulders. This disposition is what’s caused its habitat to expand.

name: Rhydon
weakness: Water, , Grass, , Ice, Fighting, Ground, Steel
version_x: The horn of a Rhydon is powerful enough to crush raw diamonds. These Pokémon polish their horns by bashing them together.
version_y: It evolved to walk using only its hind legs, which has allowed it to expand its habitat even onto steep mountains.

name: Chansey
version_x: This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.
version_y: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.

name: Tangela
version_x: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.
version_y: The vines of a Tangela have a distinct scent. In some parts of Galar, Tangela vines are used as herbs.

name: Kangaskhan
version_x: Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.
version_y: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.

name: Horsea
version_x: If attacked—even by a large enemy—Horsea effortlessly swims to safety by utilizing its well-developed dorsal fin.
version_y: It maintains balance using its tail, which is wound up like a coil. It may spray ink from its mouth.

name: Seadra
version_x: The male raises the young. If it is approached while caring for young, it will use its toxic spines to fend off the intruder.
version_y: Its fin tips leak poison. Its fins and bones are highly valued as ingredients in herbal medicine.

name: Goldeen
version_x: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.
version_y: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.

name: Seaking
version_x: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.
version_y: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

name: Staryu
version_x: If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you’ll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.
version_y: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn’t bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

name: Starmie
version_x: This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.
version_y: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

name: Mr. Mime
version_x: It is a pantomime expert that can create invisible but solid walls using miming gestures.
version_y: Emanations from its fingertips solidify the air into invisible walls that repel even harsh attacks.

name: Scyther
version_x: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.
version_y: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

name: Jynx
weakness: Fire, Bug, Rock, Ghost, Dark, Steel
version_x: In certain parts of Galar, Jynx was once feared and worshiped as the Queen of Ice.
version_y: The Jynx of Galar often have beautiful and delicate voices. Some of these Pokémon have even gathered a fan base.

name: Electabuzz
version_x: Its body constantly discharges electricity. Getting close to it will make your hair stand on end.
version_y: Research is progressing on storing lightning in Electabuzz so this energy can be used at any time.

name: Magmar
version_x: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather’s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.
version_y: Wavering flames similar to those of the sun appear on the surface of this Pokémon’s body.

name: Pinsir
version_x: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.
version_y: This Pokémon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.

name: Tauros
version_x: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.
version_y: They fight each other by locking horns. The herd’s protectors take pride in their battle-scarred horns.

name: Magikarp
version_x: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.
version_y: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

name: Gyarados
version_x: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.
version_y: It appears whenever there is world conflict, burning down any place it travels through.

name: Lapras
version_x: It ferries people across the sea on its back. It may sing an enchanting cry if it is in a good mood.
version_y: Able to understand human speech and very intelligent, it loves to swim in the sea with people on its back.

name: Ditto
version_x: Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can’t maintain its disguise.
version_y: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.

name: Eevee
version_x: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.
version_y: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element stones.

name: Vaporeon
version_x: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.
version_y: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it can’t be seen when it melts away into water.

name: Jolteon
version_x: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.
version_y: If agitated, it uses electricity to straighten out its fur and launch it in small bunches.

name: Flareon
version_x: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.
version_y: It fluffs out its fur collar to cool down its body temperature, which can reach 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
version_x: It is an artificial Pokémon. Since it doesn’t breathe, people are excited by its potential to be useful in any environment.
version_y: Porygon is an artificial Pokémon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely through cyberspace.

name: Omanyte
version_x: Because some Omanyte manage to escape after being restored or are released into the wild by people, this species is becoming a problem.
version_y: This Pokémon is a member of an ancient, extinct species. Omanyte paddles through water with its 10 tentacles, looking like it’s just drifting along.

name: Omastar
version_x: Weighed down by a large and heavy shell, Omastar couldn’t move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.
version_y: Omastar’s sharp fangs could crush rock, but the Pokémon can attack only the prey that come within reach of its tentacles.

name: Kabuto
version_x: This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days, making their shells harder and harder.
version_y: While some say this species has gone extinct, Kabuto sightings are apparently fairly common in some places.

name: Kabutops
version_x: Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokémon.
version_y: The cause behind the extinction of this species is unknown. Kabutops were aggressive Pokémon that inhabited warm seas.

name: Aerodactyl
version_x: This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.
version_y: Aerodactyl’s sawlike fangs can shred skin to tatters—even the skin of Steel-type Pokémon.

name: Snorlax
version_x: This gluttonous Pokémon eats constantly, apart from when it’s asleep. It devours nearly 900 pounds of food per day.
version_y: Its stomach’s digestive juices can dissolve any kind of poison. Eating things off the ground doesn’t bother it at all.

name: Articuno
version_x: This legendary bird Pokémon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.
version_y: This legendary bird Pokémon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

name: Zapdos
version_x: This legendary Pokémon is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
version_y: This legendary Pokémon is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

name: Moltres
version_x: It is one of the legendary bird Pokémon. Its appearance is said to indicate the coming of spring.
version_y: It is one of the legendary bird Pokémon. Its appearance is said to indicate the coming of spring.

name: Dratini
version_x: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.
version_y: It is born large to start with. It repeatedly sheds its skin as it steadily grows longer.

name: Dragonair
version_x: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.
version_y: It is called the divine Pokémon. When its entire body brightens slightly, the weather changes.

name: Dragonite
version_x: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.
version_y: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.

name: Mewtwo
version_x: Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.
version_y: Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

name: Mew
version_x: When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.
version_y: When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.

name: Chikorita
version_x: It loves to bask in the sunlight. It uses the leaf on its head to seek out warm places.
version_y: Its pleasantly aromatic leaf has the ability to check the humidity and temperature of the area around it.

name: Bayleef
version_x: The spicy scent that wafts from around Bayleef’s neck somehow makes those who smell it want to fight.
version_y: The scent that wafts from the leaves on its neck causes anyone who smells it to become energetic.

name: Meganium
version_x: Anyone who stands beside it becomes refreshed, just as if they were soaking in the soothing atmosphere of a forest.
version_y: Meganium’s breath holds within it the power to revive grasses and plants that have withered.

name: Cyndaquil
version_x: It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised, it shoots flames out of its back.
version_y: The fire that spouts from its back burns hottest when it is angry. The flaring flames intimidate foes.

name: Quilava
version_x: Before battle, it turns its back on its opponent to demonstrate how ferociously its fire blazes.
version_y: The fur covering this Pokémon’s body never burns, no matter what. It can shrug off any kind of fire attack.

name: Typhlosion
version_x: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur to cause huge explosions.
version_y: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

name: Totodile
version_x: Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.
version_y: This rough critter chomps at any moving object it sees. Turning your back on it is not recommended.

name: Croconaw
version_x: The tips of its fangs are slanted backward. Once those fangs clamp down, the prey has no hope of escape.
version_y: It opens its huge jaws wide to attack. If it loses fangs while biting, they’ll just keep on growing back, one after another.

name: Feraligatr
version_x: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.
version_y: Although it has a massive body, its powerful hind legs enable it to move quickly, even on land.

name: Sentret
version_x: This Pokémon is extremely cautious. Its supple tail is well muscled and firm to the touch.
version_y: If it encounters a foe, it will stand up on its tail, making itself look bigger than usual to intimidate them.

name: Furret
version_x: It raises its offspring inside a long, narrow nest. Once they’re old enough, it takes them outside the nest to prepare them for independence.
version_y: It is nimble and has a very flexible body. Even if you get ahold of it, it’ll slip right out of your arms.

name: Hoothoot
version_x: Hoothoot’s internal clock is precise at all times. It tilts its head in a fixed rhythm.
version_y: Since it tells time precisely, some countries consider it to be a deity of wisdom, versed in the ways of the world.

name: Noctowl
version_x: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.
version_y: Its extremely soft wings make no sound in flight. It silently sneaks up on prey without being detected.

name: Ledyba
version_x: This Pokémon is very sensitive to cold. In the warmth of Alola, it appears quite lively.
version_y: These very cowardly Pokémon join together and use Reflect to protect their nest.

name: Ledian
version_x: It’s said that the patterns on its back are related to the stars in the night sky, but the details of that relationship remain unclear.
version_y: It flies through the night sky, sprinkling sparkly dust. According to some, if that dust sticks to you, good things will happen to you.

name: Spinarak
version_x: Even while there are prey ensnared in its nest of spun thread, Spinarak will wait motionlessly until darkness falls.
version_y: Some fishers weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

name: Ariados
version_x: A single strand of a special thread is endlessly spun out of its rear. The thread leads back to its nest.
version_y: It wanders in search of food after darkness falls, never nesting in a specific place.

name: Crobat
version_x: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target’s neck.
version_y: This Pokémon flaps its four wings skillfully. Crobat can fly through cramped caves without needing to slow down.

name: Chinchou
version_x: It lives in ocean depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.
version_y: It shoots positively and negatively charged electricity from the tips of its two antennae and stuns its opponents.

name: Lanturn
version_x: Portions of its dorsal fin mutated, becoming the parts that glow brightly to lure prey.
version_y: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light. With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon swallows it in a single gulp.

name: Pichu
version_x: It is unskilled at storing electric power. Any kind of shock causes it to discharge energy spontaneously.
version_y: Despite this Pokémon’s cute appearance, those who want to live with one should prepare to be on the receiving end of its electric jolts.

name: Cleffa
version_x: On late nights illuminated by shooting stars, it gazes intently skyward, as if thinking of its home.
version_y: Since it is often seen when shooting stars fill the night skies, it’s said to come here by riding on a star.

name: Igglybuff
version_x: Its body has a faintly sweet scent and is bouncy and soft. If it bounces even once, it cannot stop.
version_y: It likes to sing but is not yet good at it. With praise and encouragement, it will get better little by little.

name: Togepi
version_x: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.
version_y: It is considered to be a symbol of good luck. Its shell is said to be filled with happiness.

name: Togetic
version_x: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.
version_y: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.

name: Natu
version_x: It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.
version_y: Because its wings aren’t yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.

name: Xatu
version_x: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.
version_y: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.

name: Mareep
version_x: If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.
version_y: Its fleece grows continually. In the summer, the fleece is fully shed, but it grows back in a week.

name: Flaaffy
version_x: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won’t grow.
version_y: Because of its rubbery, electricity-resistant skin, it can store lots of electricity in its fur.

name: Ampharos
version_x: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.
version_y: When it gets dark, the light from its bright, shiny tail can be seen from far away on the ocean’s surface.

name: Bellossom
version_x: Due to the effects of the Sun Stone, it is now active during the daytime. It likes to dance in pools of sunlight.
version_y: After it grows up, it leaves the forest it was born in to form groups with other Bellossom. It breaks into dance when it gets excited.

name: Marill
version_x: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.
version_y: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it’s fine even in rivers with strong currents.

name: Azumarill
version_x: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.
version_y: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.

name: Sudowoodo
version_x: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.
version_y: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.

name: Politoed
version_x: If Poliwag and Poliwhirl hear its echoing cry, they respond by gathering from far and wide.
version_y: It’s the leader of Poliwag and Poliwhirl. When Politoed roars, they all cower in fear.

name: Hoppip
version_x: This Pokémon is blown across vast distances by the wind. It is unclear where the Hoppip of Paldea originally came from.
version_y: Outside of cold regions, Hoppip can be found practically everywhere. This is because the wind carries this species all over the world.

name: Skiploom
version_x: Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokémon’s head.
version_y: When the weather grows cold, Skiploom’s flower closes and the Pokémon cannot photosynthesize, so it flies away to warmer regions.

name: Jumpluff
version_x: Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does its life.
version_y: Beware its cotton spores. If you accidentally breathe them in, you’ll be racked with coughs and itchiness.

name: Aipom
version_x: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.
version_y: Its tail moves with greater dexterity than its hands. Making deft use of this tail, Aipom lives high among the treetops.

name: Sunkern
version_x: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. Knowing it’s weak, it simply feeds until it evolves.
version_y: It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.

name: Sunflora
version_x: In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic manner, but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.
version_y: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.

name: Yanma
version_x: As Yanma surveys its territory, it periodically stops to hover in place by flapping its wings at high speeds.
version_y: It can see in all directions without moving its big eyes, helping it spot both attackers and prey right away.

name: Wooper
version_x: A transparent mucous membrane covers its body. Touching it bare-handed will cause a tingling numbness.
version_y: When it walks around on land, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.

name: Quagsire
version_x: This carefree Pokémon has an easygoing nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.
version_y: Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on riverbed boulders and boat hulls as it swims.

name: Espeon
version_x: The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is predicting its opponent’s next move.
version_y: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy’s actions.

name: Umbreon
version_x: When exposed to the moon’s aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.
version_y: When darkness falls, the rings on the body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.

name: Murkrow
version_x: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.
version_y: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.

name: Slowking
version_x: When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke’s head and unlocked an extraordinary power.
version_y: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.

name: Misdreavus
version_x: This Pokémon startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.
version_y: It loves to bite and yank people’s hair from behind without warning, just to see their shocked reactions.

name: Unown
version_x: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.
version_y: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

name: Wobbuffet
version_x: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.
version_y: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

name: Girafarig
version_x: Though very small, the brain in its tail is still considered an important organ because it emits powerful psychic energy.
version_y: Girafarig’s tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon from behind.

name: Pineco
version_x: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn’t bother it.
version_y: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.

name: Forretress
version_x: It’s usually found hanging on to a fat tree trunk. It shoots out bits of its shell when it sees action.
version_y: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.

name: Dunsparce
version_x: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.
version_y: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can float just slightly using its wings.

name: Gligar
version_x: It builds its nest on a steep cliff. When it is done gliding, it hops along the ground back to its nest.
version_y: It glides as if sliding. It startles foes by clamping on to their faces, then jabs with its poison stinger.

name: Steelix
version_x: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.
version_y: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.

name: Snubbull
version_x: In truth, it is a cowardly Pokémon. It growls eagerly in order to hide its fear from its opponent.
version_y: Its growls make its opponents uneasy. This laid-back Pokémon tends to sleep half the day.

name: Granbull
version_x: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked, it desperately flails its limbs about in an attempt to repel its opponent.
version_y: It can make most any Pokémon run away by opening its big mouth to reveal its thick fangs.

name: Qwilfish
version_x: Be cautious if this Pokémon starts sucking in water—it will soon attack by scattering the toxic spikes that grow all over its body.
version_y: Experienced fishers say they try to catch Qwilfish in the brief moment that these Pokémon become defenseless just after launching poisonous spikes.

name: Scizor
version_x: This Pokémon’s pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object they get ahold of into bits.
version_y: It swings its eye-patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.

name: Shuckle
version_x: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.
version_y: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

name: Heracross
version_x: It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.
version_y: With its herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

name: Sneasel
weakness: Fire, Fighting, , Bug, Rock, Steel, Fairy
version_x: This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.
version_y: This is a smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.

name: Teddiursa
version_x: This Pokémon discreetly follows Combee to find their hive. It scoops up big dollops of honey in its palms to eat.
version_y: Its paws are soaked in oodles of honey. When nervous, Teddiursa will lick its paws and soon have a smile back on its face.

name: Ursaring
version_x: It usually wears a hardened expression, but when it’s licking up honey—which it loves—the joy it feels will cause it to break into a wide grin.
version_y: It is quite skilled at climbing trees. If it comes across a Primeape while searching for berries in the treetops, trouble will surely ensue.

name: Slugma
version_x: Its lava body can cool and chip away at times, but a magma bath will heal it right up.
version_y: It’s said that in ancient times, when volcanoes were more active, there were many more Slugma than there are now.

name: Magcargo
version_x: This Pokémon lives near the craters of volcanoes. It stores fire energy in its shell of cooled and hardened magma.
version_y: According to folklore, a sudden increase in the wild Magcargo population heralds a volcanic eruption.

name: Swinub
version_x: It searches for food by digging into the ground with its snout. Even frozen ground doesn’t give it any trouble.
version_y: It rubs its snout against the ground, digging through the soil as it searches for food. Sometimes it digs up hot springs.

name: Piloswine
version_x: Covered by a shaggy coat, it is resistant to the cold. Its tusks of ice thicken when it snows.
version_y: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.

name: Corsola
version_x: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.
version_y: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.

name: Remoraid
version_x: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.
version_y: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine’s underside to scavenge for leftovers.

name: Octillery
version_x: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.
version_y: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

name: Delibird
version_x: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.
version_y: It always carries its food with it, wherever it goes. If attacked, it throws its food at the opponent.

name: Mantine
version_x: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.
version_y: As it majestically swims, it doesn’t care if Remoraid attach to it to scavenge for its leftovers.

name: Skarmory
version_x: Its sturdy, heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.
version_y: Since the feathers that it sheds are thin and sharp, people apparently once used them as swords.

name: Houndour
version_x: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.
version_y: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

name: Houndoom
version_x: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.
version_y: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

name: Kingdra
version_x: It sleeps deep on the ocean floor to build its energy. It is said to cause tornadoes as it wakes.
version_y: This Pokémon is said to sleep at the bottom of the sea—deeper than any other life-form can descend—building its energy.

name: Phanpy
version_x: This Pokémon lives and nests on a riverbank. After playing in the mud, it won’t be able to settle down unless it washes its body.
version_y: It is far stronger than it appears. If a Phanpy is swinging its trunk around and your arm gets hit by it, your arm bone will shatter.

name: Donphan
version_x: Donphan is covered in tough hide, so even being hit by a car won’t faze this Pokémon. However, it is extremely susceptible to rain.
version_y: Donphan is normally a calm Pokémon, but once it is enraged, it will curl its body into a ball and charge at you while rolling.

name: Porygon2
version_x: This artificial Pokémon evolved thanks to cutting-edge science. It sometimes displays behavior that is not in its programming.
version_y: Porygon was upgraded to become capable of planetary development. However, this upgraded version cannot even fly yet.

name: Stantler
version_x: This Pokémon apparently used to live in much harsher environments, and thus it once had stronger psychic powers than it does now.
version_y: It’s said that this Pokémon used to be stronger long ago when it had many enemies, and that it was even able to evolve under its own power.

name: Smeargle
version_x: Once a Smeargle reaches adulthood, it will have other members of its species leave paw prints on its back.
version_y: The color of the mysterious fluid secreted from the tip of the tail is predetermined for each Smeargle.

name: Tyrogue
version_x: This earnest Pokémon battles all sorts of opponents, searching for the fighting style that suits it best.
version_y: Its intense desire to become stronger and stronger drives it to recklessly train its body and challenge any opponent it can find to battle.

name: Hitmontop
version_x: This Pokémon is adept at dance-like kicks. The horn atop its head is made from the same substance that generally forms fur and claws.
version_y: It spins on its horn while dealing out elegant kicks. Its horn grows continuously through its lifetime.

name: Smoochum
weakness: Fire, Bug, Rock, Ghost, Dark, Steel
version_x: If its face gets even slightly dirty, Smoochum will bathe immediately. But if its body gets dirty, Smoochum doesn’t really seem to care.
version_y: This is a very curious Pokémon. Smoochum decides what it likes and dislikes by touching things with its lips.

name: Elekid
version_x: It loves violent thunder. The space between its horns flickers bluish white when it is charging energy.
version_y: It rotates its arms to generate electricity, but it tires easily, so it only charges up a little bit.

name: Magby
version_x: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, sparks leak from its mouth and nostrils.
version_y: Magma-like blood circulates throughout this Pokémon’s body, raising its body temperature as high as 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Miltank
version_x: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it’s been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.
version_y: This Pokémon needs to be milked every day, or else it will fall ill. The flavor of Miltank milk changes with the seasons.

name: Blissey
version_x: Anyone who takes even one taste of Blissey’s egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.
version_y: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

name: Raikou
version_x: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.
version_y: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

name: Entei
version_x: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.
version_y: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

name: Suicune
version_x: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.
version_y: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

name: Larvitar
weakness: Water, , Grass, , Ice, Fighting, Ground, Steel
version_x: Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.
version_y: It is born deep underground. It can’t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.

name: Pupitar
weakness: Water, , Grass, , Ice, Fighting, Ground, Steel
version_x: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.
version_y: Its shell is as hard as bedrock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.

name: Tyranitar
weakness: Water, Grass, Fighting, , Ground, Bug, Steel, Fairy
version_x: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn’t care about others.
version_y: In just one of its mighty hands, it has the power to make the ground shake and mountains crumble.

name: Lugia
version_x: Lugia’s wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.
version_y: Lugia’s wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

name: Ho-Oh
version_x: Ho-Oh’s feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.
version_y: Ho-Oh’s feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

name: Celebi
weakness: Fire, Ice, Poison, Flying, Bug, , Ghost, Dark
version_x: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.
version_y: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

name: Treecko
version_x: The small hooks on the soles of its feet latch on to walls and ceilings, so it will never fall even while hanging upside down.
version_y: Treecko can quickly scale even vertical surfaces. It senses humidity with its tail to predict the next day’s weather.

name: Grovyle
version_x: Its strongly developed thigh muscles give it astounding agility and jumping performance.
version_y: Grovyle leaps from branch to branch in large trees, moving with ease. It propels itself with astounding speed and force.

name: Sceptile
version_x: It agilely flits through the jungle and uses the sharp-edged leaves on its arms to cut down its prey.
version_y: The leaves on its arms are as sharp as swords. It agilely leaps about the branches of trees to strike its enemies.

name: Torchic
version_x: Torchic feels toasty warm if you hug it. It has a flame sac inside its belly, and the flames burn continuously as long as Torchic has life in it.
version_y: In its belly, it has a sac filled with burning fire, meaning that Torchic feels as warm as a hot-water bottle if you hug it.

name: Combusken
version_x: It boosts its concentration by emitting harsh cries. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.
version_y: When it enters battle, the flame inside its body burns stronger. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

name: Blaziken
version_x: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.
version_y: It can jump powerfully, clearing a 30-story building in a single leap. Its flaming punches scorch its opponents.

name: Mudkip
version_x: It has the power to crush large boulders into pieces. To rest, it buries itself in mud at the bottom of a river.
version_y: When it uses its large tail fin, it picks up speed rapidly in the water. It is strong in spite of its small size.

name: Marshtomp
version_x: Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has served to train its lower body and caused it to develop sturdy legs.
version_y: It is at its best when on muddy ground that offers poor footing. It quickly overwhelms opponents that are bogged down and unable to move.

name: Swampert
version_x: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing, it can break an enormous boulder into pieces.
version_y: Swampert’s arms are rock-hard. With one swing, they can batter down Swampert’s foes. This Pokémon makes its nest on beautiful beaches.

name: Poochyena
version_x: It bares its large fangs and barks vigorously to try to intimidate opponents, but this is actually a manifestation of its cowardly nature.
version_y: Poochyena pursue their prey in packs. Once the prey is exhausted, the pack finishes it off. But sometimes the prey retaliates, and the pack flees.

name: Mightyena
version_x: They faithfully follow the orders of their leader. Prey targeted by Mightyena is never allowed to escape the outstanding teamwork of its pursuers.
version_y: Once it’s caught the scent of faraway prey, the leader gives a signal, and the whole pack moves out.

name: Zigzagoon
version_x: It walks in zigzag fashion. It’s good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.
version_y: It walks in zigzag fashion. It’s good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.

name: Linoone
version_x: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.
version_y: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

name: Wurmple
version_x: Using the spikes on its rear end, Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokémon’s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.
version_y: Wurmple is targeted by Swellow as prey. This Pokémon will try to resist by pointing the spikes on its rear at the attacking predator. It will weaken the foe by leaking poison from the spikes.

name: Silcoon
version_x: Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.
version_y: Silcoon was thought to endure hunger and not consume anything before its evolution. However, it is now thought that this Pokémon slakes its thirst by drinking rainwater that collects on its silk.

name: Beautifly
version_x: Beautifly’s favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokémon, just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.
version_y: Beautifly has a long mouth like a coiled needle, which is very convenient for collecting pollen from flowers. This Pokémon rides the spring winds as it flits around gathering pollen.

name: Cascoon
version_x: Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.
version_y: If it is attacked, Cascoon remains motionless however badly it may be hurt. It does so because if it were to move, its body would be weak upon evolution. This Pokémon will also not forget the pain it endured.

name: Dustox
version_x: Dustox is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this Pokémon are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.
version_y: When Dustox flaps its wings, a fine dust is scattered all over. This dust is actually a powerful poison that will even make a pro wrestler sick. This Pokémon searches for food using its antennae like radar.

name: Lotad
version_x: The leaf on its head is naturally dirt repellent and will stay clean even after transporting Pokémon that are covered in mud.
version_y: Lotad will gather in lakes that have good water quality. The surfaces of these lakes sometimes become covered in Lotad leaves.

name: Lombre
version_x: Old folklore in Kitakami tells of a mischievous child who was reborn as a Pokémon.
version_y: It prefers waterfronts with plentiful food. It became nocturnal so it wouldn’t have to compete for food with bird Pokémon.

name: Ludicolo
version_x: There are structures throughout its whole body that produce energy when hit by sound waves with a cheerful rhythm.
version_y: Dancing with an upbeat rhythm energizes and emboldens it, letting it face any foe without fear.

name: Seedot
version_x: To expand its habitat, it pretends to be a nut so that bird Pokémon will pick it up and carry it far away.
version_y: Seedot live in trees, hanging from the branches and leeching moisture. Rows of them can be found dangling from large, young trees.

name: Nuzleaf
weakness: Fire, Ice, Fighting, Poison, Flying, Bug, , Fairy
version_x: It leads a quiet life deep in the forest. If anything wanders into its territory, Nuzleaf will warn the intruder by sounding its grass flute.
version_y: Its sensory functions are concentrated in its pointed nose, which it uses to sense its surroundings. The nose is also its weak point.

name: Shiftry
weakness: Fire, Ice, Fighting, Poison, Flying, Bug, , Fairy
version_x: It is said that when Shiftry flaps its leafy fans atop ancient trees, chilly winds blow and the season rolls into winter.
version_y: Legends tell of a bird Pokémon that received divine punishment for its evil deeds and had its beak and wings replaced.

name: Taillow
version_x: Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokémon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.
version_y: Taillow is young—it has only just left its nest. As a result, it sometimes becomes lonesome and cries at night. This Pokémon feeds on Wurmple that live in forests.

name: Swellow
version_x: Swellow flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokémon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow’s clawed feet, preventing escape.
version_y: Swellow is very conscientious about the upkeep of its glossy wings. Once two Swellow are gathered, they diligently take care of cleaning each other’s wings.

name: Wingull
version_x: It soars high in the sky, riding on updrafts like a glider. It carries food tucked in its bill.
version_y: It rides upon ocean winds as if it were a glider. In the winter, it hides food around its nest.

name: Pelipper
version_x: It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.
version_y: It protects its young in its beak. It bobs on waves, resting on them on days when the waters are calm.

name: Ralts
version_x: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.
version_y: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.

name: Kirlia
version_x: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.
version_y: The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.

name: Gardevoir
version_x: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.
version_y: It unleashes psychokinetic energy at full power when protecting a Trainer it has bonded closely with.

name: Surskit
version_x: They usually live on ponds, but after an evening shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.
version_y: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.

name: Masquerain
version_x: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction—to and fro and sideways.
version_y: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.

name: Shroomish
version_x: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.
version_y: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.

name: Breloom
weakness: Fire, Ice, Poison, Flying, , Psychic, Fairy
version_x: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.
version_y: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.

name: Slakoth
version_x: It sleeps for 20 hours every day. Making drowsy those that see it is one of its abilities.
version_y: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.

name: Vigoroth
version_x: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.
version_y: It is always hungry because it won’t stop rampaging. Even while it is eating, it can’t keep still.

name: Slaking
version_x: It is the world’s most slothful Pokémon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.
version_y: This Pokémon lives lying on its side. It only rolls over and moves when there is no more grass to eat.

name: Nincada
version_x: Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.
version_y: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

name: Ninjask
version_x: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.
version_y: This Pokémon is so quick, it is said to be able to avoid any attack. It loves to feed on tree sap.

name: Shedinja
version_x: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.
version_y: A strange Pokémon—it flies without moving its wings, has a hollow shell for a body, and does not breathe.

name: Whismur
version_x: The cry of a Whismur is over 100 decibels. If you’re close to a Whismur when it lets out a cry, you’ll be stuck with an all-day headache.
version_y: When Whismur cries, the sound of its own voice startles it, making the Pokémon cry even louder. It cries until it’s exhausted, then it falls asleep.

name: Loudred
version_x: Loudred’s ears serve as speakers, and they can put out sound waves powerful enough to blow away a house.
version_y: The force of this Pokémon’s loud voice isn’t just the sound—it’s also the wave of air pressure that blows opponents away and damages them.

name: Exploud
version_x: In the past, people would use the loud voices of these Pokémon as a means of communication between distant cities.
version_y: This Pokémon can do more than just shout. To communicate with others of its kind, it’ll emit all sorts of sounds from the holes in its body.

name: Makuhita
version_x: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.
version_y: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.

name: Hariyama
version_x: It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.
version_y: It stomps on the ground to build power. It can send a 10-ton truck flying with a straight-arm punch.

name: Azurill
version_x: Its tail bounces like a rubber ball. It flings that tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.
version_y: Its tail is packed full of the nutrients it needs to grow.

name: Nosepass
version_x: The magnet in Nosepass’s nose provides an unerring compass, making this Pokémon an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.
version_y: When endangered, it may protect itself by increasing its magnetism and drawing nearby iron objects to its body.

name: Skitty
version_x: Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.
version_y: Skitty is known to chase around playfully after its own tail. In the wild, this Pokémon lives in holes in the trees of forests. It is very popular as a pet because of its adorable looks.

name: Delcatty
version_x: Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.
version_y: Delcatty sleeps anywhere it wants without keeping a permanent nest. If other Pokémon approach it as it sleeps, this Pokémon will never fight—it will just move away somewhere else.

name: Sableye
version_x: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.
version_y: Materials from gems it has eaten float to the surface of its body and can form an infinite number of patterns among individuals.

name: Mawile
version_x: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.
version_y: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

name: Aron
version_x: It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks— to build up the steel armor that protects its body.
version_y: When Aron evolves, its steel armor peels off. In ancient times, people would collect Aron’s shed armor and make good use of it in their daily lives.

name: Lairon
version_x: Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore, so these Pokémon often came into conflict with humans in the past.
