version_y: During territorial disputes, Lairon fight by slamming into each other. Close inspection of their steel armor reveals scratches and dents.

name: Aggron
version_x: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.
version_y: Long ago, there was a king who wore a helmet meant to resemble the head of an Aggron. He was trying to channel the Pokémon’s strength.

name: Meditite
version_x: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.
version_y: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

name: Medicham
version_x: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe’s next move.
version_y: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.

name: Electrike
version_x: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.
version_y: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

name: Manectric
version_x: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.
version_y: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.

name: Plusle
version_x: It cheers on partners while scattering sparks from its body. It climbs telephone poles to absorb electricity.
version_y: This Pokémon absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out the electricity stored inside its body to create noises.

name: Minun
version_x: Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.
version_y: Its dislike of water makes it take shelter under the eaves of houses in rain. It uses pom-poms made of sparks for cheering.

name: Volbeat
version_x: It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.
version_y: It flashes the light on its rear to communicate with other Volbeat. It loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.

name: Illumise
version_x: Illumise uses its sweet scent to guide Volbeat, having them form over 200 patterns in the night sky.
version_y: It guides Volbeat to draw signs in the night sky. There are scholars who research the meaning of these signs.

name: Roselia
version_x: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.
version_y: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

name: Gulpin
version_x: There is nothing its stomach can’t digest. While it is digesting, vile, overpowering gases are expelled.
version_y: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.

name: Swalot
version_x: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.
version_y: It can swallow a tire whole in one gulp. It secretes a horribly toxic fluid from the pores on its body.

name: Carvanha
version_x: It won’t attack while it’s alone—not even if it spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to join it, and then the Pokémon attack as a group.
version_y: These Pokémon have sharp fangs and powerful jaws. Sailors avoid Carvanha dens at all costs.

name: Sharpedo
version_x: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.
version_y: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sea. Any ship entering the waters Sharpedo calls home will be attacked—no exceptions.

name: Wailmer
version_x: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.
version_y: When it sucks in a large volume of seawater, it becomes like a big, bouncy ball. It eats a ton of food daily.

name: Wailord
version_x: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.
version_y: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

name: Numel
version_x: Magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. When it grows cold, the magma hardens and slows it.
version_y: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.

name: Camerupt
version_x: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.
version_y: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.

name: Torkoal
version_x: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.
version_y: Coal is the source of Torkoal’s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.

name: Spoink
version_x: Spoink will die if it stops bouncing. The pearl on its head amplifies its psychic powers.
version_y: Using its tail like a spring, it keeps its heart beating by bouncing constantly. If it stops, it dies.

name: Grumpig
version_x: It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.
version_y: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes’ minds.

name: Spinda
version_x: Its steps are shaky and stumbling. Walking for a long time makes it feel sick.
version_y: Each Spinda’s spot pattern is different. With its stumbling movements, it evades opponents’ attacks brilliantly!

name: Trapinch
version_x: This Pokémon lives in arid deserts. It patiently awaits prey inside its funnel-shaped nest.
version_y: As it digs through the sand, its giant jaws crush any rocks that obstruct its path. It builds a funnel-shaped nest.

name: Vibrava
version_x: Rather than using its underdeveloped wings for flight, it rubs them together, emitting ultrasonic waves to attack its enemies.
version_y: It generates ultrasonic waves by vigorously vibrating its wings. After making its prey faint, it dissolves the prey with its digestive juices.

name: Flygon
version_x: Known as the Desert Spirit, this Pokémon hides in the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.
version_y: The sound of its wings flapping resembles singing. Those entranced by this sound get lured into a sandstorm and become Flygon’s prey.

name: Cacnea
version_x: It prefers harsh environments, such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.
version_y: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.

name: Cacturne
weakness: Fire, Ice, Fighting, Poison, Flying, Bug, , Fairy
version_x: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.
version_y: It lives in deserts. It becomes active at night when it hunts for prey exhausted from the desert’s heat.

name: Swablu
version_x: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.
version_y: It can’t relax if it or its surroundings are not clean. It wipes off dirt with its wings.

name: Altaria
version_x: If it bonds with a person, it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings, then hum.
version_y: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.

name: Zangoose
version_x: It’s Seviper’s archrival. To threaten those it encounters, it fans out the claws on its front paws.
version_y: If it comes across a Seviper, its fur bristles and it assumes its battle pose. Its sharp claws are its best weapon.

name: Seviper
version_x: It sharpens its swordlike tail on hard rocks. It hides in tall grass and strikes unwary prey with venomous fangs.
version_y: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It’s Zangoose’s archrival.

name: Lunatone
weakness: Water, Grass, Ground, Bug, Ghost, Dark, Steel
version_x: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It’s active on the night of a full moon.
version_y: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.

name: Solrock
weakness: Water, Grass, Ground, Bug, Ghost, Dark, Steel
version_x: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.
version_y: Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.

name: Barboach
version_x: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey’s location.
version_y: It probes muddy riverbeds with its two long whiskers. A slimy film protects its body.

name: Whiscash
version_x: It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.
version_y: Sighting Whiscash leaping from the water is believed to herald an earthquake.

name: Corphish
version_x: It came from overseas. It is a very hardy creature that will quickly proliferate, even in polluted streams.
version_y: It can live in impure water, where it doesn’t need to compete with other water Pokémon for food, so its numbers have steadily increased.

name: Crawdaunt
version_x: Loving to battle, this Pokémon pinches all Pokémon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.
version_y: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

name: Baltoy
weakness: Water, Grass, Ice, Bug, Ghost, Dark
version_x: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.
version_y: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

name: Claydol
weakness: Water, Grass, Ice, Bug, Ghost, Dark
version_x: This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.
version_y: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

name: Lileep
version_x: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.
version_y: Lileep clings to rocks on the seabed. When prey comes close, this Pokémon entangles it with petallike tentacles.

name: Cradily
version_x: It has short legs and can’t walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.
version_y: Once Cradily catches prey in its tentacles, it digests them whole and absorbs their nutrients.

name: Anorith
version_x: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Anorith lived in the ocean about 100,000,000 years ago, hunting with its pair of claws.
version_y: Anorith can swim swiftly by pulling its eight wings through the water like oars on a boat. This Pokémon is an ancestor of modern bug Pokémon.

name: Armaldo
version_x: After evolution, this Pokémon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger, and blows from its tail are devastating.
version_y: Though it lives on land, it’s also a good swimmer. It dives into the ocean in search of prey, using its sharp claws to take down its quarry.

name: Feebas
version_x: This tough Pokémon is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn’t popular.
version_y: It is the shabbiest Pokémon of all. It forms schools and lives at the bottom of rivers that teem with plant life.

name: Milotic
version_x: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow-colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.
version_y: It lives at the bottom of clear lakes. In times of war, it shows itself, which soothes people’s minds and hearts.

name: Castform
version_x: Although its form changes with the weather, that is apparently the result of a chemical reaction and not the result of its own free will.
version_y: Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform’s disposition!

name: Kecleon
version_x: It changes its hue to blend into its surroundings. If no one takes notice of it for too long, it will pout and never reveal itself.
version_y: Its color changes for concealment and also when its mood or health changes. The darker the color, the healthier it is.

name: Shuppet
version_x: It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice. Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.
version_y: It feeds on the dark emotions of sadness and hatred, which make it grow steadily stronger.

name: Banette
version_x: This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.
version_y: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.

name: Duskull
version_x: In the dead of night, these Pokémon wander through towns in search of children, whose vital energy is a Duskull’s favorite food.
version_y: Duskull’s victims suffer an intense chill as the Pokémon siphons their life-force away, glaring at them with its bright red eye all the while.

name: Dusclops
version_x: Dusclops is feared because it’s said to pull the soul out of anyone who gazes upon the strange movements of its hands.
version_y: Dusclops’s true form is said to be a bright red eye burning within its body, but no one has ever seen such a thing.

name: Tropius
version_x: It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.
version_y: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.

name: Chimecho
version_x: It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.
version_y: Its cries echo inside its hollow body to emerge as beautiful notes for startling and repelling foes.

name: Absol
version_x: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.
version_y: Because of this Pokémon’s ability to detect danger, people mistook Absol as a bringer of doom.

name: Wynaut
version_x: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.
version_y: It tends to move in a pack with others. They cluster in a tight group to sleep in a cave.

name: Snorunt
version_x: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.
version_y: It is said that a home visited by a Snorunt will prosper. It can withstand cold of −150 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Glalie
version_x: Its prey is instantaneously frozen stiff by the cold air it exhales from its huge mouth. While they’re in that frozen state, it gobbles them up.
version_y: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.

name: Spheal
version_x: This Pokémon’s body is covered in blubber and impressively round. It’s faster for Spheal to roll around than walk.
version_y: As it drifts among the waves, Spheal probes the sea. As soon as it spots prey, it informs the Walrein in its herd.

name: Sealeo
version_x: Sealeo live on top of drift ice. They go swimming when they’re on the hunt, seeking out their prey by scent.
version_y: This Pokémon has a habit of spinning round things on its nose, whether those things are Poké Balls or Spheal.

name: Walrein
version_x: Walrein form herds of 20 to 30 individuals. When a threat appears, the herd’s leader will protect the group with its life.
version_y: Walrein’s tusks keep growing throughout its life. Tusks broken in battle will grow back to their usual impressive size in a year.

name: Clamperl
version_x: Despite its appearance, it’s carnivorous. It clamps down on its prey with both sides of its shell and doesn’t let go until they stop moving.
version_y: Clamperl’s pearls are exceedingly precious. They can be more than 10 times as costly as Shellder’s pearls.

name: Huntail
version_x: It’s not the strongest swimmer. It wags its tail to lure in its prey and then gulps them down as soon as they get close.
version_y: Deep seas are their habitat. According to tradition, when Huntail wash up onshore, something unfortunate will happen.

name: Gorebyss
version_x: The color of its body changes with the water temperature. The coloration of Gorebyss in Alola is almost blindingly vivid.
version_y: It sucks bodily fluids out of its prey. The leftover meat sinks to the seafloor, where it becomes food for other Pokémon.

name: Relicanth
version_x: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.
version_y: This Pokémon was discovered during deep-sea exploration. Its appearance hasn’t changed in 100,000,000 years, so it’s called a living fossil.

name: Luvdisc
version_x: Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places, you would give a Luvdisc to someone you love.
version_y: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.

name: Bagon
version_x: Its steel-hard head can shatter boulders. It longingly hopes for wings to grow so it can fly.
version_y: Its belief that it will be able to fly one day is apparently the influence of information carried in its genes.

name: Shelgon
version_x: The cells within its shell transform with explosive speed, preparing it for evolution.
version_y: Its armored body makes all attacks bounce off. The armor is too tough, however, making it heavy and somewhat sluggish.

name: Salamence
version_x: It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up everything it passes over.
version_y: It becomes uncontrollable if it is enraged. It destroys everything with shredding claws and fire.

name: Beldum
version_x: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground’s natural magnetism, letting it float.
version_y: All its cells are magnets. It communicates with others of its kind by transmitting magnetic forces from its body.

name: Metang
version_x: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.
version_y: It adores magnetic minerals, so it pursues Nosepass at speeds exceeding 60 mph.

name: Metagross
version_x: It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.
version_y: It firmly pins its prey using its four claws and large body. Then Metagross uses the mouth on its stomach to chew its prey to bits.

name: Regirock
version_x: Every bit of Regirock’s body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks rocks to itself to repair what’s been lost.
version_y: Cutting-edge technology was used to study the internals of this Pokémon’s rock body, but nothing was found—not even a brain or a heart.

name: Regice
version_x: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as −328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.
version_y: This Pokémon’s body is made of solid ice. It’s said that Regice was born beneath thick ice in the ice age.

name: Registeel
version_x: Registeel’s body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.
version_y: It’s rumored that this Pokémon was born deep underground in the planet’s mantle and that it emerged onto the surface 10,000 years ago.

name: Latias
weakness: Ice, Bug, Ghost, Dragon, Dark, Fairy
version_x: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.
version_y: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

name: Latios
weakness: Ice, Bug, Ghost, Dragon, Dark, Fairy
version_x: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.
version_y: Latios will only open its heart to a Trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

name: Kyogre
version_x: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.
version_y: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

name: Groudon
version_x: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.
version_y: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.

name: Rayquaza
version_x: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.
version_y: It flies forever through the ozone layer, consuming meteoroids for sustenance. The many meteoroids in its body provide the energy it needs to Mega Evolve.

name: Jirachi
version_x: A legend states that Jirachi will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this Pokémon senses danger, it will fight without awakening.
version_y: Jirachi will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

name: Deoxys
version_x: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokémon’s chest appears to be its brain.
version_y: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

name: Turtwig
version_x: The shell on its back is made of soil. If the shell is moist to the touch, Turtwig is very healthy.
version_y: It uses its whole body to photosynthesize when exposed to sunlight. Its shell is made from hardened soil.

name: Grotle
version_x: Grotle live in the forest. Each is said to have its own secret place for getting clean springwater.
version_y: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

name: Torterra
version_x: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground dwelt a gigantic Torterra.
version_y: Some Pokémon are born on a Torterra’s back and spend their entire life there.

name: Chimchar
version_x: It is very agile. Before going to sleep, it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.
version_y: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

name: Monferno
version_x: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.
version_y: A bigger fire on its tail and a brighter blue pattern on its face means it holds a higher rank in its troop.

name: Infernape
version_x: This Pokémon confounds opponents with its speed. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.
version_y: It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its hands and feet. It will take on any opponent.

name: Piplup
version_x: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.
version_y: It doesn’t like to be taken care of. It’s difficult to bond with since it won’t listen to its Trainer.

name: Prinplup
version_x: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees in half with a single hit.
version_y: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.

name: Empoleon
version_x: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them in two with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.
version_y: It avoids unnecessary disputes, but it will mercilessly decimate anything that threatens the safety of its colony.

name: Starly
version_x: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.
version_y: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.

name: Staravia
version_x: Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.
version_y: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.

name: Staraptor
version_x: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.
version_y: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.

name: Bidoof
version_x: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.
version_y: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

name: Bibarel
version_x: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.
version_y: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

name: Kricketot
version_x: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.
version_y: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

name: Kricketune
version_x: By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly, it produces a captivating sound.
version_y: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.

name: Shinx
version_x: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.
version_y: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it’s in trouble.

name: Luxio
version_x: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.
version_y: By gathering their tails together, they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.

name: Luxray
version_x: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.
version_y: Luxray’s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it’s scouting for danger.

name: Budew
version_x: The pollen it releases contains poison. If this Pokémon is raised on clean water, the poison’s toxicity is increased.
version_y: This Pokémon is highly sensitive to temperature changes. When its bud starts to open, that means spring is right around the corner.

name: Roserade
version_x: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.
version_y: The poison in its right hand is quick acting. The poison in its left hand is slow acting. Both are life threatening.

name: Cranidos
version_x: It lived in jungles around a hundred million years ago. It used its skillful headbutts to combat Aerodactyl.
version_y: Cranidos toughen up their already sturdy heads by headbutting one another.

name: Rampardos
version_x: Stifled by a thick skull that can withstand any impact, this Pokémon’s brain never got very big.
version_y: If two were to smash their heads together, their foot-thick skulls would keep them from fainting.

name: Shieldon
version_x: It is outstandingly armored. As a result, it has no particular need to battle with others and can spend its time feeding on grass and berries.
version_y: This Pokémon lived in primeval jungles. It’s thought that Shieldon had few enemies thanks to its sturdy face.

name: Bastiodon
version_x: While it can guard against any sort of attack from the front, it is left without recourse when attacked from behind.
version_y: Bastiodon live in herds. When assaulted by enemies, they line up side by side and use their hard faces to block attacks.

name: Burmy
version_x: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.
version_y: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

name: Wormadam
weakness: Fire, , Ice, Poison, Flying, , Bug, Rock
version_x: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.
version_y: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

name: Mothim
version_x: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.
version_y: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

name: Combee
version_x: At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a hundred, packed closely together in a lump.
version_y: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers nectar from flowers to please Vespiquen.

name: Vespiquen
version_x: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.
version_y: It raises grubs in the holes in its body. It secretes pheromones to control Combee.

name: Pachirisu
version_x: It’s one of the kinds of Pokémon with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.
version_y: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

name: Buizel
version_x: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.
version_y: It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.

name: Floatzel
version_x: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.
version_y: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and help fishers carry what they caught.

name: Cherubi
version_x: It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked by bird Pokémon that would love to make off with its small, nutrient-rich storage ball.
version_y: The deeper a Cherubi’s red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

name: Cherrim
version_x: As a bud, it barely moves. It sits still, placidly waiting for sunlight to appear.
version_y: Its folded petals are pretty tough. Bird Pokémon can peck at them all they want, and Cherrim won’t be bothered at all.

name: Shellos
version_x: It used to have a shell on its back long ago. This species is closely related to Pokémon like Shellder.
version_y: It oozes a purple fluid to deter enemies. Apparently, there are more West Sea Shellos now than there were in the past.

name: Gastrodon
version_x: Its whole body is sticky with mucus. In the past, this form of Gastrodon was by far the more numerous one.
version_y: It appears on beaches where the waters are shallow. Once it catches prey, it will slowly melt them with its mucus before slurping them up.

name: Ambipom
version_x: They live on large trees. They are said to communicate by connecting their tails to those of others.
version_y: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things that Ambipom rarely uses its hands.

name: Drifloon
version_x: It is whispered that any child who mistakes Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.
version_y: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a “signpost for wandering spirits.”

name: Drifblim
version_x: It can generate and release gas within its body. That’s how it can control the altitude of its drift.
version_y: They carry people and Pokémon, but the wind can catch them, so there can’t be a fixed destination.

name: Buneary
version_x: If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, something is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the Pokémon is in need of care.
version_y: Buneary can attack by rolling up their ears and then striking with the force created by unrolling them. This attack becomes stronger with training.

name: Lopunny
version_x: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds with superdestructive kicks.
version_y: Once hot seasons are over, Lopunny’s coat will be replaced with fur that holds a lot of insulating air in preparation for colder weather.

name: Mismagius
version_x: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.
version_y: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

name: Honchkrow
version_x: It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.
version_y: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than 100 of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.

name: Glameow
version_x: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.
version_y: When it’s happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

name: Purugly
version_x: It would claim another Pokémon’s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.
version_y: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

name: Chingling
version_x: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.
version_y: It emits high-frequency cries that people can’t hear. Once it starts, it can cry for an awfully long time.

name: Stunky
version_x: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.
version_y: The foul fluid from its rear is so revolting that it can make people feel queasy up to a mile and a quarter away.

name: Skuntank
version_x: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.
version_y: It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail, but the stench dulls after a few squirts.

name: Bronzor
version_x: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor’s back contained a mysterious power.
version_y: They are found in ancient tombs. The patterns on their backs are said to be imbued with mysterious power.

name: Bronzong
version_x: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.
version_y: It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.

name: Bonsly
version_x: In order to adjust the level of fluids in its body, it exudes water from its eyes. This makes it appear to be crying.
version_y: From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from its body. This liquid is similar in composition to human sweat.

name: Mime Jr.
version_x: It mimics everyone it sees, but it puts extra effort into copying the graceful dance steps of Mr. Rime as practice.
version_y: It looks for a Mr. Rime that’s a good dancer and carefully copies the Mr. Rime’s steps like an apprentice.

name: Happiny
version_x: It carries a round, white rock in its belly pouch. If it gets along well with someone, it will sometimes give that person the rock.
version_y: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It’s bothered by how curly its hair looks.

name: Chatot
version_x: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t attack it.
version_y: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: Spiritomb
version_x: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.
version_y: It was formed by uniting 108 spirits. It has been bound to the Odd Keystone to keep it from doing any mischief.

name: Gible
version_x: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.
version_y: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.

name: Gabite
version_x: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.
version_y: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.

name: Garchomp
version_x: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.
version_y: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.

name: Munchlax
version_x: It needs to consume its own weight in food every day. As far as flavor is concerned, it’s indifferent.
version_y: When it is voraciously gulping down food, it forgets about the food it has hidden under its fur.

name: Riolu
version_x: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.
version_y: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions, such as joy and rage, in the form of waves.

name: Lucario
version_x: It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those of foes it could not otherwise see.
version_y: A well-trained one can use its aura to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.

name: Hippopotas
version_x: It shuts its nostrils tight, then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.
version_y: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.

name: Hippowdon
version_x: It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.
version_y: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.

name: Skorupi
version_x: After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokémon and Sizzlipede share common descent.
version_y: It attacks using the claws on its tail. Once locked in its grip, its prey is unable to move as this Pokémon’s poison seeps in.

name: Drapion
version_x: Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead, going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.
version_y: It’s so vicious that it’s called the Sand Demon. Yet when confronted by Hippowdon, Drapion keeps a low profile and will never pick a fight.

name: Croagunk
version_x: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.
version_y: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.

name: Toxicroak
version_x: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges out with its poisonous claws.
version_y: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.

name: Carnivine
version_x: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.
version_y: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

name: Finneon
version_x: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.
version_y: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.

name: Lumineon
version_x: With its shining light, it lures its prey close. However, the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokémon—its natural predators.
version_y: Lumineon swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.

name: Mantyke
version_x: Mantyke living in Galar seem to be somewhat sluggish. The colder waters of the seas in this region may be the cause.
version_y: It swims along with a school of Remoraid, and they’ll all fight together to repel attackers.

name: Snover
weakness: Fire, , Fighting, Poison, Flying, Bug, Rock, Steel
version_x: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain’s lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.
version_y: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.

name: Abomasnow
weakness: Fire, , Fighting, Poison, Flying, Bug, Rock, Steel
version_x: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.
version_y: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.

name: Weavile
weakness: Fire, Fighting, , Bug, Rock, Steel, Fairy
version_x: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.
version_y: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.

name: Magnezone
version_x: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.
version_y: Exposure to a special magnetic field changed Magneton’s molecular structure, turning it into Magnezone.

name: Lickilicky
version_x: Lickilicky’s strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky’s tongue can stretch so far.
version_y: Lickilicky can do just about anything with its tongue, which is as dexterous as the human hand. In contrast, Lickilicky’s use of its fingers is clumsy.

name: Rhyperior
weakness: Water, , Grass, , Ice, Fighting, Ground, Steel
version_x: This Pokémon’s sturdy carapace protects it from volcanic eruptions. It shoots round rocks from the holes in its hands.
version_y: A Rhyperior’s brain is smaller than a Rhydon’s, but the Rhyperior is stronger because it spends more energy on battling and less on brainpower.

name: Tangrowth
version_x: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.
version_y: Vine growth is accelerated for Tangrowth living in warm climates. If the vines grow long, Tangrowth shortens them by tearing parts of them off.

name: Electivire
version_x: When it gets excited, it thumps its chest. With every thud, thunder roars and electric sparks shower all around.
version_y: This Pokémon presses the tips of its tails onto an opponent and instantly sends over 20,000 volts of high-voltage electricity through them.

name: Magmortar
version_x: When shooting 3,600 degree Fahrenheit fireballs from its arms, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.
version_y: They dwell in volcanic craters. It’s said that only a single pair of Magmortar will inhabit any given volcano.

name: Togekiss
version_x: These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they’ve hardly been seen at all.
version_y: Known as a bringer of blessings, it’s been depicted on good-luck charms since ancient times.

name: Yanmega
version_x: Yanmega’s wingbeats are so powerful that the Pokémon blows down huge trees nearby when it vigorously launches itself into flight.
version_y: Its jaw power is incredible. It is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed.

name: Leafeon
version_x: When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of sunshine, you’ll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.
version_y: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.

name: Glaceon
version_x: It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.
version_y: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

name: Gliscor
version_x: If it succeeds in catching even a faint breeze properly, it can circle the globe without flapping once.
version_y: It flies soundlessly through the sky. It catches prey with its long tail, then lunges at the prey’s vulnerable spots with its fangs.

name: Mamoswine
version_x: A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice dating back 10,000 years. This Pokémon has been around a long, long, long time.
version_y: A frozen one was dug up from soil dating back 10,000 years. It woke up, to much amazement.

name: Porygon-Z
version_x: An additional program was installed to create a more advanced Pokémon, but it was apparently flawed. Porygon-Z moves oddly as a result.
version_y: Its programming was modified to enable it to operate in other dimensions. This did not work as planned.

name: Gallade
version_x: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.
version_y: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.

name: Probopass
version_x: It controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force. With them, it can attack a foe from three directions.
version_y: Probopass radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances are rendered useless while it’s around.

name: Dusknoir
version_x: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and take them to the afterlife.
version_y: It comes and goes between this world and the afterlife. People fear this Pokémon because it is said to suck in lost spirits and take them along.

name: Froslass
version_x: When it finds humans or Pokémon it likes, it freezes them and takes them to its chilly den, where they become decorations.
version_y: It freezes prey by blowing its −58 degree Fahrenheit breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.

name: Rotom
version_x: Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.
version_y: Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.

name: Uxie
version_x: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.
version_y: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.

name: Mesprit
version_x: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.
version_y: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake’s surface.

name: Azelf
version_x: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.
version_y: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

name: Dialga
version_x: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.
version_y: This Pokémon is spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

name: Palkia
version_x: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.
version_y: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. Palkia appears in mythology.

name: Heatran
version_x: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.
version_y: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

name: Regigigas
version_x: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.
version_y: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

name: Giratina
version_x: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.
version_y: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

name: Cresselia
version_x: When it flies, it releases shiny particles from its veil-like wings. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
version_y: When it flies, it releases shiny particles from its veil-like wings. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Phione
version_x: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.
version_y: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

name: Manaphy
version_x: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.
version_y: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Darkrai
version_x: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.
version_y: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Shaymin
version_x: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.
version_y: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

name: Arceus
version_x: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.
version_y: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

name: Victini
version_x: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
version_y: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.

name: Snivy
version_x: The leaf on Snivy’s tail generates energy when exposed to sunlight, making Snivy swifter and adding an edge to its moves.
version_y: It prefers to avoid groups. In its day-to-day life, it dexterously controls its vines to compensate for its short arms.

name: Servine
version_x: It runs low to the ground, weaving through the grass, then mercilessly pummels its target by whipping them with its vines.
version_y: Servine’s one weakness is its inflated sense of pride. It takes a while for Servine to be able to cooperate with other Pokémon.

name: Serperior
version_x: It generates energy from sunlight, then amplifies that energy dozens of times within its long body.
version_y: An intimidating gaze and majestic appearance have caused this Pokémon to be known as the Lord of the Forest.

name: Tepig
version_x: It’s more nimble than it looks, and it uses its speed to confound its enemies. It rapidly launches fireballs from both nostrils.
version_y: This Pokémon is a ravenous glutton. It uses its excellent sense of smell to find food, then cooks it to a crisp before eating.

name: Pignite
version_x: When Pignite enters battle, its body temperature rapidly soars until Pignite itself is engulfed by a scorching fireball.
version_y: When defending its friends, Pignite will stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong. But it’s powerless when faced with an empty stomach.

name: Emboar
version_x: The flames blazing deep inside Emboar’s chest erupt vigorously from its chin, forming a beard of fire.
version_y: The direr the situation, the more it seems to enjoy itself. The flames around its neck intensify, too, increasing Emboar’s power and speed.

name: Oshawott
version_x: It wields the scalchop on its stomach like a knife, blocking the moves of its enemies before slashing back at them in swift retaliation.
version_y: It’s said that Oshawott learned to maintain its scalchop with riverbed stones by mimicking humans it saw using whetstones.

name: Dewott
version_x: It’s said that people modeled swordplay after the way Dewott’s movements flow like water while it’s wielding its two scalchops.
version_y: Dewott has a studious and stern personality. It masters the use of its scalchops through dedicated, repeated training.

name: Samurott
version_x: A master of a sword-drawing art called iaijutsu, Samurott settles its battles with a single swing of either large sword sheathed in its foreleg armor.
version_y: Samurott leads its group strictly. Those who do not follow its rules receive a merciless thrashing.

name: Patrat
version_x: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.
version_y: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won’t notice a foe coming from behind.

name: Watchog
version_x: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.
version_y: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: Lillipup
version_x: This Pokémon is courageous but also cautious. It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect information about its surroundings.
version_y: This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won’t forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.

name: Herdier
version_x: Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokémon. So much so that there’s a theory that Herdier was the first Pokémon to partner with people.
version_y: The black fur that covers this Pokémon’s body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.

name: Stoutland
version_x: These Pokémon seem to enjoy living with humans. Even a Stoutland caught in the wild will warm up to people in about three days.
version_y: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It’s said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.

name: Purrloin
version_x: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.
version_y: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

name: Liepard
version_x: Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.
version_y: This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.

name: Pansage
version_x: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.
version_y: It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.

name: Simisage
version_x: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokémon is wild tempered.
version_y: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Pansear
version_x: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.
version_y: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Simisear
version_x: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.
version_y: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

name: Panpour
version_x: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.
version_y: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

name: Simipour
version_x: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.
version_y: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: Munna
version_x: Late at night, it appears beside people’s pillows. As it feeds on dreams, the patterns on its body give off a faint glow.
version_y: It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it’s eating a good dream, and black when it’s eating a nightmare.

name: Musharna
version_x: When dark mists emanate from its body, don’t get too near. If you do, your nightmares will become reality.
version_y: It drowses and dreams all the time. It’s best to leave it be if it’s just woken up, as it’s a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.

name: Pidove
version_x: Where people go, these Pokémon follow. If you’re scattering food for them, be careful—several hundred of them can gather at once.
version_y: It’s forgetful and not very bright, but many Trainers love it anyway for its friendliness and sincerity.

name: Tranquill
version_x: It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels, it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.
version_y: These bright Pokémon have acute memories. Apparently delivery workers often choose them as their partners.

name: Unfezant
version_x: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.
version_y: This Pokémon is intelligent and intensely proud. People will sit up and take notice if you become the Trainer of one.

name: Blitzle
version_x: Its heartbeat generates electricity. When Blitzle is surprised and its heart rate goes up, the voltage of its electricity also rises.
version_y: This Pokémon prefers places with lots of lightning strikes. It catches lightning with its mane and stores the electricity within its body.

name: Zebstrika
version_x: This Pokémon is aggressive and has a volatile disposition. When agitated, it will illuminate its mane in yellow and fire off bolts of electricity.
version_y: Once the herd hears thunder, it chases after the storm clouds so that the Blitzle in the group can use the lightning to charge up.

name: Roggenrola
version_x: It’s as hard as steel, but apparently a long soak in water will cause it to soften a bit.
version_y: When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.

name: Boldore
version_x: If you see its orange crystals start to glow, be wary. It’s about to fire off bursts of energy.
version_y: It relies on sound in order to monitor what’s in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it’s facing.

name: Gigalith
version_x: This hardy Pokémon can often be found on construction sites and in mines, working alongside people and Copperajah.
version_y: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation—they can only be fired when the sun is out.

name: Woobat
version_x: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it’s evidence that Woobat live there.
version_y: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.

name: Swoobat
version_x: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won’t be able to fly for a little while.
version_y: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon’s nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.

name: Drilbur
version_x: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.
version_y: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.

name: Excadrill
version_x: Forming a drill with its steel claws and head, it can bore through a steel plate, no matter how thick it is.
version_y: Its drill, which has evolved into steel, is strong enough to bore through iron plates. This Pokémon is a great help in tunnel construction.

name: Audino
version_x: Audino’s sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino’s ears.
version_y: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.

name: Timburr
version_x: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.
version_y: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle heavy lumber without difficulty.

name: Gurdurr
version_x: They strengthen their bodies by carrying steel beams. They show off their big muscles to their friends.
version_y: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: Conkeldurr
version_x: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.
version_y: Rather than rely on their strength, they master moves that make good use of centrifugal force to swing around concrete.

name: Tympole
version_x: Graceful ripples running across the water’s surface are a sure sign that Tympole are singing in high-pitched voices below.
version_y: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can’t hear its cries of warning.

name: Palpitoad
version_x: It weakens its prey with sound waves intense enough to cause headaches, then entangles them with its sticky tongue.
version_y: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.

name: Seismitoad
version_x: The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.
version_y: This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.

name: Throh
version_x: It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles, Throh’s belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer’s sweat.
version_y: They train in groups of five. Any member that can’t keep up will discard its belt and leave the group.

name: Sawk
version_x: If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength, it’s best to quietly pass by.
version_y: The karate chops of a Sawk that’s trained itself to the limit can cleave the ocean itself.

name: Sewaddle
weakness: Fire, , Ice, Poison, Flying, , Bug, Rock
version_x: Sewaddle chews on leaves to make its clothing. It’s trying to mimic the leafy garment Leavanny first dressed it in.
version_y: The bumps on their heads are sensory organs. When Sewaddle meet, they greet each other by rubbing these bumps together.

name: Swadloon
weakness: Fire, , Ice, Poison, Flying, , Bug, Rock
version_x: Swadloon lives quietly at the feet of trees. It prefers eating fallen leaves that have grown soft rather than fresh ones.
version_y: Swadloon wraps itself in leaves for protection. It uses the two leaves atop its head to detect air movements and feel out its surroundings.

name: Leavanny
weakness: Fire, , Ice, Poison, Flying, , Bug, Rock
version_x: This gentle Pokémon has strong protective instincts. The leaves on its arms are sharp enough to slice a thick tree in half with one stroke.
version_y: It fashions clothing from woven leaves. Though gentle in disposition, it will show no mercy to foes who target young Pokémon.

name: Venipede
version_x: Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species, but when the two meet, a huge fight ensues.
version_y: Its fangs are highly venomous. If this Pokémon finds prey it thinks it can eat, it leaps for them without any thought of how things might turn out.

name: Whirlipede
version_x: This Pokémon spins itself rapidly and charges into its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.
version_y: Whirlipede protects itself with a sturdy shell and poisonous spikes while it stores up the energy it’ll need for evolution.

name: Scolipede
version_x: Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on its neck before slamming them into the ground and jabbing them with its claws’ toxic spikes.
version_y: Scolipede engage in fierce territorial battles with Centiskorch. At the end of one of these battles, the victor makes a meal of the loser.

name: Cottonee
version_x: Pillows and beds stuffed with cotton exhaled by Cottonee are soft and puffy, light and airy—altogether top quality.
version_y: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

name: Whimsicott
version_x: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.
version_y: It rides on the wind and slips into people’s homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton-filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.

name: Petilil
version_x: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.
version_y: If the leaves on its head are pruned with regularity, this Pokémon can be grown into a fine plump shape.

name: Lilligant
version_x: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.
version_y: No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.

name: Basculin
version_x: Its temperament is vicious and aggressive. This Pokémon is also full of vitality and can multiply rapidly before anyone notices.
version_y: It’s so vicious that it’s called the Thug of the River. Yet Basculin is still targeted by predators, such as Dondozo and Bombirdier.

name: Sandile
weakness: Water, Grass, Ice, Fighting, Bug, Fairy
version_x: It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.
version_y: They live hidden under hot desert sands in order to keep their body temperature from dropping.

name: Krokorok
weakness: Water, Grass, Ice, Fighting, Bug, Fairy
version_x: Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see even in the dead of night. They live in groups of a few individuals.
version_y: Thanks to the special membrane covering its eyes, it can see its surroundings clearly, even in the middle of the night.

name: Krookodile
weakness: Water, Grass, Ice, Fighting, Bug, Fairy
version_x: After clamping down with its powerful jaws, it twists its body around to rip its prey in half.
version_y: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.

name: Darumaka
version_x: Darumaka’s droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.
version_y: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Darmanitan
version_x: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.
version_y: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

name: Maractus
version_x: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.
version_y: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They’re jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.

name: Dwebble
version_x: When it finds a stone appealing, it creates a hole inside it and uses it as its home. This Pokémon is the natural enemy of Roggenrola and Rolycoly.
version_y: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.

name: Crustle
version_x: This highly territorial Pokémon prefers dry climates. It won’t come out of its boulder on rainy days.
version_y: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They’re mighty enough to crack Rhyperior’s carapace.

name: Scraggy
version_x: It stretches its saggy skin up to its neck to protect itself. Among Scraggy, individuals with saggier skin apparently garner more respect.
version_y: It will abruptly headbutt anyone that makes eye contact with it. Its skull is extremely hard.

name: Scrafty
version_x: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.
version_y: This Pokémon may be rude, but it takes very good care of its family, its friends, and its turf.

name: Sigilyph
version_x: Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians’ emissaries.
version_y: A discovery was made in the desert where Sigilyph fly. The ruins of what may have been an ancient city were found beneath the sands.

name: Yamask
version_x: It wanders through ruins by night, carrying a mask that’s said to have been the face it had when it was still human.
version_y: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.

name: Cofagrigus
version_x: This Pokémon has a body of sparkling gold. People say it no longer remembers that it was once human.
version_y: There are many depictions of Cofagrigus decorating ancient tombs. They’re symbols of the wealth that kings of bygone eras had.

name: Tirtouga
version_x: This Pokémon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl, it still comes up onto land in search of prey.
version_y: Tirtouga is considered to be the ancestor of many turtle Pokémon. It was restored to life from a fossil.

name: Carracosta
version_x: Carracosta completely devours its prey—bones, shells, and all. Because of this, Carracosta’s own shell grows thick and sturdy.
version_y: This Pokémon emerges from the water in search of prey despite the fact that it moves more slowly on land.

name: Archen
version_x: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. As research suggested, Archen is unable to fly. But it’s very good at jumping.
version_y: Archen is said to be the ancestor of bird Pokémon. It lived in treetops, eating berries and bug Pokémon.

name: Archeops
version_x: It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly, it first needs to run nearly 25 mph, building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.
version_y: Though capable of flight, Archeops was apparently better at hunting on the ground.

name: Trubbish
version_x: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.
version_y: This Pokémon was born from a bag stuffed with trash. Galarian Weezing relish the fumes belched by Trubbish.

name: Garbodor
version_x: This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.
version_y: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.

name: Zorua
version_x: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.
version_y: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

name: Zoroark
version_x: Stories say those who tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.
version_y: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

name: Minccino
version_x: When its tail has gotten dirty from self-cleaning or from cleaning its nest, Minccino spends a whole day washing its tail in clean springwater.
version_y: These Pokémon like things neat and tidy. They are always sweeping and dusting their habitat, using their tails as brooms.

name: Cinccino
version_x: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.
version_y: The oil that seeps from its body is really smooth. For people troubled by bad skin, this oil is an effective treatment.

name: Gothita
version_x: This Pokémon is normally very innocent. When it is staring at something invisible, it is unblinking and utterly silent.
version_y: Beware of touching the ribbon-shaped feelers that control its psychic power. Gothita will begin bawling if you do.

name: Gothorita
version_x: This Pokémon will hypnotize children to put them to sleep before carrying them away. Be wary of nights when the starlight is bright.
version_y: Using its psychic power, it arranges pebbles to form the shapes of constellations. Some people believe this Pokémon came from outer space.

name: Gothitelle
version_x: Gothitelle unleashes psychic energy and shows opponents dreams of the universe’s end. These dreams are apparently ethereal and beautiful.
version_y: It gazes at the stars to predict the future. It acts somewhat detached because it has seen the end of all existence.

name: Solosis
version_x: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they can survive in any environment.
version_y: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: Duosion
version_x: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.
version_y: When their brains, now divided in two, are thinking the same thoughts, these Pokémon exhibit their maximum power.

name: Reuniclus
version_x: Their arms are made of a special liquid. They use psychic power to control these arms and crush boulders.
version_y: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: Ducklett
version_x: It’s not very good at flying yet. It watches the dances of its Swanna parents to learn how to move its wings.
version_y: It strengthens its body by diving into the depths of ponds, swimming around while looking for bog moss to eat.

name: Swanna
version_x: Centered around its leader, the flock dances in perfect sync to strengthen its unity.
version_y: It’s said that many artists have taken inspiration from the sight of a Swanna performing a beautiful dance in the light of dawn.

name: Vanillite
version_x: Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.
version_y: Supposedly, this Pokémon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at −58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.

name: Vanillish
version_x: By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body. This Pokémon can be hard to find on days with warm, sunny weather.
version_y: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching −148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward—it’s a kind Pokémon.

name: Vanilluxe
version_x: When its anger reaches a breaking point, this Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it, be they friend or foe.
version_y: People believe this Pokémon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Deerling
weakness: Fire, Ice, Fighting, Poison, Flying, Bug
version_x: Deerling have different scents depending on the season. In early spring, these Pokémon give off a delicate, sweet, and calming scent.
version_y: Despite Deerling’s adorable appearance, farmers consider it a nuisance since it loves plant shoots and will eat them all up.

name: Sawsbuck
weakness: Fire, Ice, Fighting, Poison, Flying, Bug
version_x: It seems that a Sawsbuck with many flowers on its antlers will grow at a slightly slower pace because the flowers absorb the Pokémon’s nutrients.
version_y: There are many Sawsbuck enthusiasts. The paler the pink flowers that bloom on its antlers, the more beautiful the Sawsbuck is considered to be.

name: Emolga
version_x: As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles with electricity. This Pokémon is cute, but it can cause a lot of trouble.
version_y: This Pokémon absolutely loves sweet berries. Sometimes it stuffs its cheeks full of so much food that it can’t fly properly.

name: Karrablast
version_x: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.
version_y: It spits a liquid from its mouth to melt through Shelmet’s shell. Karrablast doesn’t eat the shell— it eats only the contents.

name: Escavalier
version_x: They use shells they’ve stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They’re very popular Pokémon in the Galar region.
version_y: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch’d.

name: Foongus
version_x: There is a theory that the developer of the modern-day Poké Ball really liked Foongus, but this has not been confirmed.
version_y: This Pokémon prefers damp places. It spurts out poison spores to repel approaching enemies.

name: Amoonguss
version_x: Be wary of the poisonous spores it releases. Mushrooms resembling Amoonguss’s caps will grow out of anywhere the spores touch.
version_y: Amoonguss mimics Poké Balls. It is not yet clear whether this mimicry is effective against other Pokémon.

name: Frillish
version_x: It envelops its prey in its veillike arms and draws it down to the deeps, five miles below the ocean’s surface.
version_y: Legend has it that the residents of a sunken ancient city changed into these Pokémon.

name: Jellicent
version_x: Most of this Pokémon’s body composition is identical to sea water. It makes sunken ships its lair.
version_y: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.

name: Alomomola
version_x: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.
version_y: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokémon gather in the area around Alomomola.

name: Joltik
version_x: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.
version_y: Since it can’t generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.

name: Galvantula
version_x: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.
version_y: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

name: Ferroseed
version_x: It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn’t very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.
version_y: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed’s spikes grow big and strong.

name: Ferrothorn
version_x: This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.
version_y: Its spikes are harder than steel. This Pokémon crawls across rock walls by stabbing the spikes on its feelers into the stone.

name: Klink
version_x: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.
version_y: It’s suspected that Klink were the inspiration behind ancient people’s invention of the first gears.

name: Klang
version_x: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon’s rotation speed increases sharply.
version_y: Many companies in the Galar region choose Klang as their logo. This Pokémon is considered the symbol of industrial technology.

name: Klinklang
version_x: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.
version_y: The three gears that compose this Pokémon spin at high speed. Its new spiked gear isn’t a living creature.

name: Tynamo
version_x: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.
version_y: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.

name: Eelektrik
version_x: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.
version_y: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

name: Eelektross
version_x: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.
version_y: It latches on to prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.

name: Elgyem
version_x: If this Pokémon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.
