version_y: This Pokémon was discovered about 50 years ago. Its highly developed brain enables it to exert its psychic powers.

name: Beheeyem
version_x: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.
version_y: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields, this Pokémon can control the memories of its opponents.

name: Litwick
version_x: Its flame is usually out, but it starts shining when Litwick absorbs life-force from people or Pokémon.
version_y: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life-force of any who follow it.

name: Lampent
version_x: Lampent appears at the moment of death and promptly absorbs the spirit as it leaves the body.
version_y: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.

name: Chandelure
version_x: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.
version_y: It absorbs spirits, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: Axew
version_x: This Pokémon lives in nests that are made in the ground. People in ancient times used its tusks as cooking knives.
version_y: If you see peculiar teeth marks on boulders or trees, it means an Axew is likely living nearby.

name: Fraxure
version_x: Because its tusks don’t grow back once they break, this Pokémon apparently won’t use them unless truly necessary.
version_y: Fraxure uses its thick tusks to neatly cut prey into two portions—one to eat now and one to save for later.

name: Haxorus
version_x: This Pokémon nests in caves and abandoned mines. It is docile, but it will become incredibly angry if its tusks are touched, so beware.
version_y: It overwhelms enemies with its prized tusks, which are sharp enough to cut through a metal transmission tower in one strike.

name: Cubchoo
version_x: Many of this species can be found along the shorelines of cold regions. If a Cubchoo lacks dangling snot, there’s a chance it is sick.
version_y: When Cubchoo starts sneezing, watch out! If it spatters you with its frosty snot, you’ll get frostbite.

name: Beartic
version_x: It is a ferocious, carnivorous Pokémon. Once it captures its prey, it will breathe cold air onto the prey to freeze and preserve it.
version_y: Feared as the Snow-White Demon in northern lands, Beartic uses its frosty claws and fangs to attack prey.

name: Cryogonal
version_x: Cryogonal appear during cold seasons. It is said that people and Pokémon who die on snowy mountains are reborn into these Pokémon.
version_y: Cryogonal uses its chains of ice to constrict its opponents and then flash-freezes them where they stand.

name: Shelmet
version_x: When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.
version_y: It has a strange physiology that responds to electricity. When together with Karrablast, Shelmet evolves for some reason.

name: Accelgor
version_x: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.
version_y: Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.

name: Stunfisk
version_x: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.
version_y: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

name: Mienfoo
version_x: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.
version_y: They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.

name: Mienshao
version_x: When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail, you’re in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!
version_y: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

name: Druddigon
version_x: Druddigon lives in caves, but it never skips sunbathing—it won’t be able to move if its body gets too cold.
version_y: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.

name: Golett
version_x: These Pokémon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.
version_y: Its movements are powered by a mysterious energy. It has continued to move since ancient times, so its power may soon run out.

name: Golurk
version_x: When the seal on its chest is removed, it rages indiscriminately. During such rampages, it can turn a whole town into a mountain of rubble.
version_y: Golurk were created by ancient people to protect both people and Pokémon. They run on a mysterious energy.

name: Pawniard
version_x: Pawniard will fearlessly challenge even powerful foes. In a pinch, it will cling to opponents and pierce them with the blades all over its body.
version_y: Any chips in its blades would prove fatal for it. After each battle, it diligently maintains its blades using its favorite sharpening stone.

name: Bisharp
version_x: This Pokémon commands a group of several Pawniard. Groups that are defeated in territorial disputes are absorbed by the winning side.
version_y: Bisharp mercilessly cuts its opponents to pieces with the sharp blades covering its body. It will do anything to win.

name: Bouffalant
version_x: These Pokémon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.
version_y: These Pokémon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.

name: Rufflet
version_x: They pick fights indiscriminately. They grow stronger and more powerful each time they faint or are injured.
version_y: With its sharp claws, this Pokémon pierces its prey, and then it pecks at them. Although it also consumes berries, it’s a carnivore at heart.

name: Braviary
version_x: The more scars they have, the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky get from their peers.
version_y: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.

name: Vullaby
version_x: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokémon.
version_y: Its healthy appetite leads to visible growth spurts. It often has to replace the bones it wears as its size increases.

name: Mandibuzz
version_x: It’s always searching for food for Vullaby. When it finds a weak Pokémon, Mandibuzz swoops it right off to its nest.
version_y: Watching from the sky, they attack weakened prey on the ground. They have a habit of decorating themselves with bones.

name: Heatmor
version_x: There’s a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.
version_y: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.

name: Durant
version_x: They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor, they retaliate using their massive mandibles.
version_y: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

name: Deino
version_x: It can’t see, so its first approach to examining things is to bite them. You will be covered in wounds until a Deino warms up to you.
version_y: It nests deep inside a cave. Food there is scarce, so Deino will sink its teeth into anything that moves and attempt to eat it.

name: Zweilous
version_x: The two heads do not get along at all. If you don’t give each head the same amount of attention, they’ll begin fighting out of jealousy.
version_y: The two heads have different likes and dislikes. Because the heads fight with each other, Zweilous gets stronger without needing to rely on others.

name: Hydreigon
version_x: Only the central head has a brain. It is very intelligent, but it thinks only of destruction.
version_y: It’s said that Hydreigon grew ferocious because people in times long past loathed it, considering it to be evil incarnate and attacking it relentlessly.

name: Larvesta
version_x: This Pokémon was called the Larva That Stole the Sun. The fire Larvesta spouts from its horns can cut right through a sheet of iron.
version_y: In ancient times, Larvesta was worshiped as the emissary of the sun. However, it was also viewed as a burden since it often caused forest fires.

name: Volcarona
version_x: Its burning body causes it to be unpopular in hot parts of the world, but in cold ones, Volcarona is revered as an embodiment of the sun.
version_y: This Pokémon scatters burning scales. Most of the danger of these scales is not in their heat—it’s in the way they rob the surrounding air of oxygen.

name: Cobalion
version_x: This Pokémon appears in a legend alongside Terrakion and Virizion, fighting against humans in defense of the Unova region’s Pokémon.
version_y: From the moment it’s born, this Pokémon radiates the air of a leader. Its presence will calm even vicious foes.

name: Terrakion
weakness: Water, Grass, Fighting, Ground, Psychic, Steel, Fairy
version_x: It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokémon.
version_y: In Unovan legend, Terrakion battled against humans in an effort to protect other Pokémon.

name: Virizion
weakness: Fire, Ice, Poison, Flying, , Psychic, Fairy
version_x: A legend tells of this Pokémon working together with Cobalion and Terrakion to protect the Pokémon of the Unova region.
version_y: It darts around opponents with a flurry of quick movements, slicing them up with its horns.

name: Tornadus
version_x: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.
version_y: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

name: Thundurus
version_x: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.
version_y: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

name: Reshiram
version_x: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.
version_y: When Reshiram’s tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world’s weather.

name: Zekrom
version_x: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.
version_y: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

name: Landorus
version_x: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”
version_y: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

name: Kyurem
version_x: This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.
version_y: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

name: Keldeo
version_x: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.
version_y: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

name: Meloetta
version_x: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.
version_y: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

name: Genesect
version_x: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.
version_y: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

name: Chespin
version_x: When Chespin tenses up just before landing a headbutt, the spikes on its head sharpen to points, piercing the enemy’s body on contact.
version_y: Eating lots of berries makes the bark shell that covers Chespin’s head and body grow sturdier.

name: Quilladin
version_x: It’s protected by a sturdy shell. The shell is also very heavy, which naturally strengthens Quilladin’s lower body.
version_y: It can send a trailer flying with a tackle. It’s numb to pain, so even violent collisions don’t faze it.

name: Chesnaught
weakness: Fire, Ice, Poison, Flying, , Psychic, Fairy
version_x: When its allies are in trouble, Chesnaught creates a shield with its arms and uses its own body to block attacks.
version_y: Its gentle disposition would have it avoid conflict, but it gives opponents a thrashing with its thorned fists when the situation calls for it.

name: Fennekin
version_x: This Pokémon gets worked up easily. Its body can also overheat, so it uses its ears to dissipate the heat and calm down.
version_y: Twigs make for Fennekin’s snacks. When it nibbles on twigs, it finds the courage to face strong foes.

name: Braixen
version_x: It ignites the twig from its tail and waves the twig around to signal its allies. To indicate danger, it draws circles in the air with the twig’s flame.
version_y: Braixen’s branch ignites as it’s pulled from the Pokémon’s tail. Braixen then uses the flame to spark powerful attacks.

name: Delphox
version_x: It leaves burn marks in the ground with the flame at the tip of its wand. Long ago, people used the shapes of these burn marks for divination.
version_y: It controls flames telekinetically, trapping its foes in a fiery vortex surpassing 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit and burning them to a crisp.

name: Froakie
version_x: Its happy-go-lucky look is an act intended to fool its enemies. It will suddenly drop the facade and overwhelm its foes with its blinding speed.
version_y: It utilizes its extraordinary jumping abilities to flummox its foes, throwing springy bubbles at them from above their heads.

name: Frogadier
version_x: It excels at devising battle strategies that make use of the terrain, and it never misses its mark when throwing bubble-covered pebbles.
version_y: The tips of its fingers and toes stick firmly to vertical surfaces. Frogadier can scale skyscrapers with ease.

name: Greninja
version_x: The movement of air against the long tongue Greninja keeps wrapped around its neck allows it to sense enemies it can’t see.
version_y: It makes shuriken out of mucus excreted from its thighs. These shuriken can cut cleanly through steel cables.

name: Bunnelby
version_x: It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.
version_y: It’s very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight’s flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.

name: Diggersby
version_x: With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It’s a huge help during tunnel construction.
version_y: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.

name: Fletchling
version_x: This Pokémon is normally calm, but once it enters battle, its hormonal balance changes and it becomes aggressive.
version_y: Fletchling can be found in both rural and urban areas. They once had a huge territorial dispute with Squawkabilly. Fights broke out all over town.

name: Fletchinder
version_x: Fletchinder scatters embers in tall grass where bug Pokémon might be hiding and then catches them as they come leaping out.
version_y: Its territory has a radius of just over a mile. If any bird Pokémon should enter, it will show them no mercy.

name: Talonflame
version_x: It has top-notch flying capabilities. It flies around easily, even while carrying prey that weighs more than 220 lbs.
version_y: When it gets excited, it vents sparks from the gaps between its feathers. These unburnable feathers are used as a fireproof material.

name: Scatterbug
version_x: Any poison this Pokémon takes in is converted into a black powder and secreted. That’s why Scatterbug can eat poisonous leaves and roots.
version_y: This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder to repel enemies. It will eat different plants depending on where it lives.

name: Spewpa
version_x: If Rufflet attacks this Pokémon by pecking at it, it will retaliate with its sharp fur and poisonous black powder.
version_y: Spewpa doesn’t live in a fixed location. It roams where it pleases across the fields and mountains, building up the energy it needs to evolve.

name: Vivillon
version_x: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands where flowers bloom.
version_y: This Pokémon was born in a land where flowers bloom. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

name: Litleo
version_x: When Litleo are young, female Pyroar will teach them how to hunt. Once the Litleo mature, they will leave the pride and set out on their own.
version_y: The more a Litleo trains its body and spirit by battling mighty enemies, the hotter its mane will grow.

name: Pyroar
version_x: The females of a pride work together to bring down prey. It’s thanks to them that their pride doesn’t starve.
version_y: The mane of a male Pyroar heats up to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit during battle. Merely approaching it will cause severe burns.

name: Flabébé
version_x: This Pokémon can draw forth the power hidden within blooming wild flowers. It is particularly fond of red flowers.
version_y: This Flabébé rides a red flower. Immediately after birth, this Pokémon begins flying around in search of a flower it likes.

name: Floette
version_x: This Pokémon draws forth what power is left in withered flowers to make them healthy again. It holds a red flower.
version_y: This Pokémon uses red wavelengths of light to pour its own energy into flowers and draw forth their latent potential.

name: Florges
version_x: This Pokémon creates an impressive flower garden in its territory. It draws forth the power of the red flowers around its neck.
version_y: They say that flower gardens created by Florges are constantly showered with a power that can heal both body and spirit.

name: Skiddo
version_x: Until recently, people living in the mountains would ride on the backs of these Pokémon to traverse the mountain paths.
version_y: As long as it has sunlight and water, Skiddo can make energy with the leaves on its body, allowing it to live on rocky mountains barren of food.

name: Gogoat
version_x: It can sense the feelings of others by touching them with its horns. This species has assisted people with their work since 5,000 years ago.
version_y: These Pokémon live in herds in mountainous places. The victor in their contests of clashing horns will become the leader of the herd.

name: Pancham
version_x: It chooses a Pangoro as its master and then imitates its master’s actions. This is how it learns to battle and hunt for prey.
version_y: Wanting to make sure it’s taken seriously, Pancham’s always giving others a glare. But if it’s not focusing, it ends up smiling.

name: Pangoro
version_x: This Pokémon is quick to anger, and it has no problem using its prodigious strength to get its way. It lives for duels against Obstagoon.
version_y: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.

name: Furfrou
version_x: There was an era when aristocrats would compete to see who could trim their Furfrou’s fur into the most exquisite style.
version_y: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.

name: Espurr
version_x: It keeps its ears covered to prevent the intense psychic power in its body from escaping, but it falls unconscious if this power builds too much.
version_y: Behind an Espurr’s expressionless face is a frantic struggle to contain psychic power.

name: Meowstic
version_x: Though it has enough psychic power to blast away any opponent, Meowstic prefers to support its allies rather than attack.
version_y: If Meowstic continuously emits its powerful psychic energy, it will damage its own body.

name: Honedge
version_x: Honedge’s soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge’s body.
version_y: The blue eye on the sword’s handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people’s lives away.

name: Doublade
version_x: Honedge evolves into twins. The two blades rub together to emit a metallic sound that unnerves opponents.
version_y: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

name: Aegislash
version_x: In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.
version_y: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokémon to build a kingdom to its liking.

name: Spritzee
version_x: A scent pouch within this Pokémon’s body allows it to create various scents. A change in its diet will alter the fragrance it produces.
version_y: The scent its body gives off enraptures those who smell it. Noble ladies had no shortage of love for Spritzee.

name: Aromatisse
version_x: The scent that constantly emits from its fur is so powerful that this Pokémon’s companions will eventually lose their sense of smell.
version_y: The scents Aromatisse can produce range from sweet smells that bolster allies to foul smells that sap an opponent’s will to fight.

name: Swirlix
version_x: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn’t get enough sugar, it becomes incredibly grumpy.
version_y: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix’s fluffy fur. This Pokémon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.

name: Slurpuff
version_x: By taking in a person’s scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It’s hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.
version_y: Slurpuff’s fur contains a lot of air, making it soft to the touch and lighter than it looks.

name: Inkay
version_x: It protects itself from tough foes by flashing its luminescent spots to discourage them.
version_y: Being upside-down improves its blood flow and clears its mind, causing the power of its psychic moves to increase dramatically.

name: Malamar
version_x: Its hypnotic powers are dangerously strong. Anyone who falls under Malamar’s control loses their memories surrounding the event.
version_y: It flashes the luminescent spots on its body to hypnotize its opponents, gaining total control over them.

name: Binacle
version_x: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.
version_y: If the two don’t work well together, both their offense and defense fall apart. Without good teamwork, they won’t survive.

name: Barbaracle
version_x: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.
version_y: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy’s defeat.

name: Skrelp
version_x: Skrelp evades its enemies by hiding amid drifting seaweed. It eats rotten seaweed to create its poison.
version_y: This Pokémon is a poor swimmer. If it’s caught in a fierce storm, it will sometimes get washed far away and become unable to return to its home.

name: Dragalge
version_x: Using a liquid poison, Dragalge indiscriminately attacks anything that wanders into its territory. This poison can corrode the undersides of boats.
version_y: Since Finizen is the better swimmer, Dragalge will approach it under the cover of seaweed, then immobilize it with a poisonous attack.

name: Clauncher
version_x: This Pokémon launches water by detonating gas inside its right claw. It snipes flying Pokémon.
version_y: Clauncher’s claws will regrow if they fall off. The meat inside the claws is edible, but it has a distinct flavor that doesn’t appeal to all tastes.

name: Clawitzer
version_x: Clawitzer can move through the water at a speed of 60 knots by using gas inside its body to expel water from the back of its claw.
version_y: The cannonballs of seawater that Clawitzer launches from its claw are powerful enough to punch through tanker hulls.

name: Helioptile
version_x: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon’s electric moves.
version_y: The sun powers this Pokémon’s electricity generation. Interruption of that process stresses Helioptile to the point of weakness.

name: Heliolisk
version_x: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.
version_y: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.

name: Tyrunt
weakness: Ice, Fighting, Ground, Dragon, Steel, Fairy
version_x: This is an ancient Pokémon, revived in modern times. It has a violent disposition, and it’ll tear apart anything it gets between its hefty jaws.
version_y: This Pokémon is selfish and likes to be pampered. It can also inflict grievous wounds on its Trainer just by playing around.

name: Tyrantrum
weakness: Ice, Fighting, Ground, Dragon, Steel, Fairy
version_x: This Pokémon is from about 100,000,000 years ago. It has the presence of a king, vicious but magnificent.
version_y: A single bite of Tyrantrum’s massive jaws will demolish a car. This Pokémon was the king of the ancient world.

name: Amaura
weakness: Water, Grass, Fighting, , Ground, Rock, Steel,
version_x: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. In the past, it lived with others of its kind in cold lands where there were fewer predators.
version_y: Amaura is an ancient Pokémon that has gone extinct. Specimens of this species can sometimes be found frozen in ice.

name: Aurorus
weakness: Water, Grass, Fighting, , Ground, Rock, Steel,
version_x: Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It’s said that when this Pokémon howls, auroras appear in the night sky.
version_y: When gripped by rage, Aurorus will emanate freezing air, covering everything around it in ice.

name: Sylveon
version_x: This Pokémon uses its ribbonlike feelers to send a soothing aura into its opponents, erasing their hostility.
version_y: Sylveon cuts an elegant figure as it dances lightly around, feelers fluttering, but its piercing moves aim straight for its opponents’ weak spots.

name: Hawlucha
version_x: Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly leaping around using its wings—are polished in the forest where it was born and raised.
version_y: Hawlucha live quietly without flocking together. They fight constantly with their natural enemies: noisy groups of Primeape.

name: Dedenne
version_x: It’s small and its electricity-generating organ is not fully developed, so it uses its tail to absorb electricity from people’s homes and charge itself.
version_y: Dedenne emit electrical waves from the whiskers on their cheeks to communicate with each other. When low on electricity, they curl up and sleep.

name: Carbink
version_x: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It’s occasionally found during the excavation of caves.
version_y: Born from the high temperatures and pressures deep underground, it defends itself by firing beams from the jewel part of its body.

name: Goomy
version_x: Most of a Goomy’s body is water. A membrane covers the whole Pokémon to prevent it from shriveling up in dry weather.
version_y: Goomy’s horns are excellent sensory organs that cover all five of Goomy’s senses. Goomy picks up on danger from the movement of the air.

name: Sliggoo
version_x: The swirly protrusion on its back is filled with all its vital organs, such as its brain and heart.
version_y: When Sliggoo senses danger, the mucus coating its entire body becomes more concentrated—it’ll dissolve anything.

name: Goodra
version_x: It loves the rain. This mellow Pokémon can be seen walking around on the plains and in the mountains on rainy days.
version_y: This Pokémon is uncontrollable when enraged. It rampages on and on, lashing its tail with enough power to send a dump truck flying.

name: Klefki
version_x: Once it absorbs a key’s metal ions, it discards the key without a second thought. However, it will hang on to keys it favors for decades.
version_y: In the past, noble families entrusted their vault keys to a Klefki. They passed the Klefki down through the generations, taking good care of it.

name: Phantump
version_x: Legend tells that its green leaves can cure any illness. When plucked, however, the leaves will instantly wither away.
version_y: This Pokémon came to be when the spirit of a deceased child possessed a tree stump. It now wanders the forest searching for friends.

name: Trevenant
version_x: Using its roots, Trevenant connects itself to trees and monitors every corner of its forest. It uses curses to drive intruders away.
version_y: Trevenant is very kind to Pokémon living in the forest. It doesn’t even care if these Pokémon take up residence in the greenery on its head.

name: Pumpkaboo
version_x: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo’s body. They’re then moved on to the afterlife.
version_y: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokémon that see it.

name: Gourgeist
version_x: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.
version_y: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.

name: Bergmite
version_x: They live in mountainous regions of frigid cold. On rare occasions, they ride on the back of an Avalugg to cross seas and move to new habitats.
version_y: Bergmite protects itself by coating its body in ice formed by frigid air of −148 degrees Fahrenheit. It fights with Frigibax whenever they meet.

name: Avalugg
version_x: As Avalugg walks along with Bergmite on its back, it comes across pods of Cetitan. It lets them pass to avoid conflict.
version_y: This Pokémon uses its massive icy body to flatten anything that gets in its way. When it’s floating out on the ocean, it looks exactly like drift ice.

name: Noibat
version_x: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from its large ears to search for fruit to eat. It mistakes Applin for its food.
version_y: Noibat can change the frequency of its sound waves at will, and it generates ultrasonic waves of up to 200,000 hertz.

name: Noivern
version_x: Ultrasonic waves emitted by a Noivern can pulverize a large boulder. This Pokémon has a cruel disposition.
version_y: In the dark, even Hydreigon are terrified of this Pokémon. But in the light, Noivern is the one that avoids battle.

name: Xerneas
version_x: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.
version_y: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

name: Yveltal
version_x: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.
version_y: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

name: Zygarde
version_x: This is Zygarde’s form when about half of its pieces have been assembled. It plays the role of monitoring the ecosystem.
version_y: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

name: Diancie
version_x: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.
version_y: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

name: Hoopa
version_x: In its true form, it possesses a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.
version_y: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

name: Volcanion
version_x: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.
version_y: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

name: Rowlet
version_x: Silently it glides, streaking toward its targets to get close to them. Before they even notice it, it begins to pelt them with vicious kicks.
version_y: It feels relaxed in tight, dark places and has been known to nestle into its Trainer’s bag or the front of their jacket.

name: Dartrix
version_x: This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you don’t groom it diligently, it may stop listening to you.
version_y: It throws sharp feathers called blade quills at enemies or prey. It seldom misses.

name: Decidueye
version_x: It cunningly conceals arrow quills in its wings. It launches these quills with such precision that they can pierce a pebble at over a hundred yards.
version_y: It nocks its arrow quills and looses them at opponents. When it needs to hit, it pulls the vines on its hood to narrow its view and focus.

name: Litten
version_x: If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.
version_y: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

name: Torracat
version_x: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever fire spews out.
version_y: Torracat will let its Trainer coddle it once they’ve grown close, but it’s a powerful, sharp-clawed Pokémon, so its Trainer gets covered in scratches.

name: Incineroar
version_x: When its fighting spirit is set alight, the flames around its waist become especially intense.
version_y: After hurling ferocious punches and flinging furious kicks, it finishes opponents off by spewing fire from around its navel.

name: Popplio
version_x: This Pokémon can control balloons made of water. It practices diligently so it can learn to make big balloons.
version_y: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.

name: Brionne
version_x: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, then briskly bombards its enemies.
version_y: It cares deeply for its companions. When its Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery dance to try to help.

name: Primarina
version_x: To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.
version_y: Also known as a songstress, it is a sight to behold on moonlit nights when it sings in front of the colony it leads.

name: Pikipek
version_x: Using its beak to strike 16 times per second, it opens holes in even the hardest of trees.
version_y: Pikipek has strong muscles in its neck, so it won’t hurt itself even if it violently shakes its head.

name: Trumbeak
version_x: It flies around using a hundred different cries in various ways to declare its territory to others.
version_y: When it encounters foes, it launches the many seeds stored in its beak in a radial burst.

name: Toucannon
version_x: The compressed gas in Toucannon’s beak launches seeds with such force that they can shatter large boulders.
version_y: Pairs of Toucannon are considered symbols of companionship, as these Pokémon will raise the temperature of their beaks to warm each other.

name: Yungoos
version_x: Its stomach fills most of its torso. It wanders the same path every day, searching for fresh food.
version_y: It spends its waking hours searching endlessly for food. When Yungoos is hungry, its ferocity gains a certain edge.

name: Gumshoos
version_x: Once it finds signs of prey, it will patiently stake out the location, waiting until the sun goes down.
version_y: Gumshoos specializes in relentlessly tracking down prey. The simple-minded Skwovet doesn’t seem to provide Gumshoos enough challenge.

name: Grubbin
version_x: Grubbin normally live underground, but if they get unearthed by Hoothoot, they may be found gathered around electric Pokémon.
version_y: It spits sticky threads and winds them around branches, then swings nimbly from tree to tree in a pendulum-like motion.

name: Charjabug
version_x: Protected by a sturdy shell, Charjabug eats large quantities of fresh and decomposing leaf litter in order to evolve.
version_y: As it digests fallen leaves, it generates and stores electricity, which it can discharge from the tips of its jaws.

name: Vikavolt
version_x: Displaying exceptional mobility, it weaves between trees and shoots down bird Pokémon with its electromagnetic beams.
version_y: When carrying a Charjabug, Vikavolt can receive electricity from it and then rapidly fire powerful electromagnetic beams from its large jaws.

name: Crabrawler
version_x: This Pokémon punches trees and eats the berries that drop down, training itself and getting food at the same time.
version_y: If it loses its pincers, they’ll quickly regrow. The pincers are popular ingredients in paella since their shells produce a tasty soup stock.

name: Crabominable
weakness: Fire, Fighting, Flying, Psychic, Steel, Fairy
version_x: The detached pincers of these Pokémon are delicious. Some Trainers bring Lechonk into the mountains just to search for them.
version_y: Though its punches are powerful, this Pokémon’s movements are sluggish. It blows icy bubbles from its mouth to immobilize its opponents.

name: Oricorio
version_x: This Pokémon is incredibly popular, possibly because its passionate dancing is a great match with the temperament of Paldean people.
version_y: This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.

name: Cutiefly
version_x: When it senses the auras of people or Pokémon who are having fun, it will draw close and give them a painful poke with its long proboscis.
version_y: Cutiefly sucks up pollen and nectar with its long proboscis. It stores any pollen it doesn’t finish eating in its fur.

name: Ribombee
version_x: Ribombee can sense when people or Pokémon are feeling down, and it will cheer them up with handmade pollen puffs.
version_y: Pollen puffs created by skilled Ribombee can relieve fatigue, making the puffs a popular commodity.

name: Rockruff
abilities: Keen Eye, Vital Spirit, Own Tempo
version_x: This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.
version_y: This Pokémon travels in a pack with others until it grows up. When its mood turns sour, it starts striking the ground with the rocks on its neck.

name: Lycanroc
version_x: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.
version_y: It has a calm and collected demeanor. It swiftly closes in on its prey, then slices them with the rocks in its mane.

name: Wishiwashi
version_x: Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.
version_y: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.

name: Mareanie
version_x: This Pokémon wanders the seaside looking for food. It often gets electric shocks from broken Pincurchin spines that it tries to eat.
version_y: It has excellent regenerative capabilities. Legs that a Mareanie has lost have a very bitter, astringent flavor—they’re not suitable as food.

name: Toxapex
version_x: This Pokémon lives within a dome made by its own legs. Toxapex monitors its surroundings by sensing the flow of the tide through its spikes.
version_y: Toxapex gets into fierce battles with Bruxish over areas where warm ocean currents flow, but the odds are always against it.

name: Mudbray
version_x: This Pokémon covers itself in mud that it has regurgitated. The mud won’t dry out even if it’s exposed to the sun for a long time.
version_y: Though a slow walker, Mudbray is plenty strong. Its pace doesn’t change even when it’s loaded with 50 times its own body weight.

name: Mudsdale
version_x: This Pokémon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.
version_y: Its legs are fortified with mud and harder than stone, and they can reduce a large truck to scrap with one kick.

name: Dewpider
version_x: Dewpider uses sticky threads to create the water bubble that covers its head, so the bubble very rarely bursts.
version_y: It supports the water bubble that envelops its head with three of its legs. Sometimes it secretly swaps which legs are holding up the bubble.

name: Araquanid
version_x: A caring Pokémon, Araquanid carries Dewpider around inside its water bubble to protect them as it walks. It protects its food in its bubble too.
version_y: It launches sticky water bubbles. Foes who lose consciousness while trapped inside these bubbles will get torn apart by Araquanid’s gnashing jaws.

name: Fomantis
version_x: Fomantis hates having its naps interrupted. It fires off beams using energy it gathers by bathing in the sun.
version_y: Many Trainers give their Fomantis their own flowerpots so they can sunbathe in peace and quiet.

name: Lurantis
version_x: By masquerading as a bug Pokémon, it lowers the guard of actual bug Pokémon lured in by a scent of sweet flowers. Its sickles bring them down.
version_y: A lot of time and effort is required to maintain the vivid colors of its petals. This Pokémon puts its Trainer’s attentiveness to the test.

name: Morelull
version_x: Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull’s head. The caps regrow overnight.
version_y: Morelull live in forests that stay dark even during the day. They scatter flickering spores that put enemies to sleep.

name: Shiinotic
version_x: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.
version_y: If you see a light deep in a forest at night, don’t go near. Shiinotic will make you fall fast asleep.

name: Salandit
version_x: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.
version_y: Only female Salandit can produce gas laden with pheromones. Males entranced by this gas will do whatever the females tell them.

name: Salazzle
version_x: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.
version_y: When two Salazzle meet, they will use their pheromone gas to fight over the males in each other’s group.

name: Stufful
version_x: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.
version_y: The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight, but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.

name: Bewear
version_x: Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.
version_y: The moves it uses to take down its prey would make a martial artist jealous. It tucks subdued prey under its arms to carry them to its nest.

name: Bounsweet
version_x: Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled-down fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in the past, when sweeteners were scarce.
version_y: A Greedent drawn in by the sweet scent of these Pokémon will tuck the Bounsweet in among the berries in its tail and carry them all away.

name: Steenee
version_x: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.
version_y: Steenee bounces energetically through forests. If the rind that peels off its body is pulverized, it can be used to treat stomach pains.

name: Tsareena
version_x: This Pokémon is proud and aggressive. However, it is said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if someone touches the crown on its calyx.
version_y: This Pokémon launches fierce yet elegant kicks with its long, slender legs. It views Quaquaval as its rival.

name: Comfey
version_x: It uses its vine to pick flowers. The flowers that Comfey attaches to itself develop healing properties.
version_y: It prefers areas with lots of flowers. A Comfey adorned with flowers is a happy Comfey, and the flowers gain healing effects.

name: Oranguru
version_x: People used to mistake Oranguru for a human when they saw it issue command after command to the other Pokémon of the forest.
version_y: This Pokémon lives quietly in the depths of the forest. The purple, cape-like fur gets longer and longer as Oranguru ages.

name: Passimian
version_x: This Pokémon battles by throwing hard berries. It won’t obey a Trainer who throws Poké Balls without skill.
version_y: The boss chooses 10 members of the group to go out hunting. The hunting party will evenly split the food they find with the rest of the group.

name: Wimpod
version_x: It’s nature’s cleaner—it eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.
version_y: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy’s presence.

name: Golisopod
version_x: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.
version_y: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner’s meal.

name: Sandygast
version_x: If it loses its shovel, it will stick something else—like a branch—in its head to make do until it finds another shovel.
version_y: It flings sand into the eyes of its prey and tries to close in on them while they’re blinded, but since Sandygast is so slow, the prey tends to escape.

name: Palossand
version_x: The terrifying Palossand drags smaller Pokémon into its sandy body. Once its victims are trapped, it drains them of their vitality whenever it pleases.
version_y: From the hollows in its arms, it fires the bones of its victims, which are all dried up after being drained of their vitality.

name: Pyukumuku
version_x: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.
version_y: It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.

name: Type: Null
version_x: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokémon being created in the Galar region.
version_y: It was modeled after a mighty Pokémon of myth. The mask placed upon it limits its power in order to keep it under control.

name: Silvally
version_x: A solid bond of trust between this Pokémon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.
version_y: The final factor needed to release this Pokémon’s true power was a strong bond with a Trainer it trusts.

name: Minior
version_x: This Pokémon is born in the ozone layer. It falls to the ground once the outer shell enclosing its core grows heavy.
version_y: It will react when touched or called to, but it’s unknown whether such responses indicate consciousness.

name: Komala
version_x: Komala spends its entire life sleeping. It feeds on leaves that contain a potent poison only Komala can break down.
version_y: A potent anesthetic can be made by diluting Komala’s drool. This anesthetic was used for surgeries in the past.

name: Turtonator
version_x: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.
version_y: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.

name: Togedemaru
version_x: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.
version_y: When it’s in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.

name: Mimikyu
version_x: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.
version_y: Mimikyu was only recently identified as a Pokémon. Previously, people thought it was just a ghost wearing a cloth.

name: Bruxish
version_x: It grinds its teeth with great force to stimulate its brain. It fires the psychic energy created by this process from the protuberance on its head.
version_y: When sunlight reflects on the ripples created by a Bruxish grinding its teeth, the water all around sparkles brilliantly.

name: Drampa
version_x: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.
version_y: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it’s angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.

name: Dhelmise
version_x: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.
version_y: After lowering its anchor, it waits for its prey. It catches large Wailord and drains their life-force.

name: Jangmo-o
version_x: The scale atop its head is useful for both offense and defense. It bravely stands and faces its foes rather than turning tail, even if its foes are strong.
version_y: They communicate with their allies using the sounds their scales make when struck. A group of these Pokémon causes quite a racket.

name: Hakamo-o
version_x: It gets into fistfights so intense that the scales on its arms peel off. Bare arms are a sign of valiance.
version_y: It fires itself up by striking its scales with force as it dances. Its roar is a battle cry.

name: Kommo-o
version_x: It lets its arm hang, and then—quick as a flash—swings upward to land its specialty punch and send the opponent flying high into the sky.
version_y: It bashes its scales to test its opponents’ mettle. The sound of struck Kommo-o scales frightens weaker foes and sends them running.

name: Tapu Koko
version_x: Although it’s called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.
version_y: The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.

name: Tapu Lele
version_x: It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.
version_y: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.

name: Tapu Bulu
version_x: Although it’s called a guardian deity, it’s violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.
version_y: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let others know where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts. This guardian deity of Ula’ula controls plants.

name: Tapu Fini
version_x: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.
version_y: Although it’s called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.

name: Cosmog
version_x: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.
version_y: Whether or not it’s a Pokémon from this world is a mystery. When it’s in a jam, it warps away to a safe place to hide.

name: Cosmoem
version_x: The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the “cocoon of the stars” and built an altar to worship it.
version_y: As it absorbs light, Cosmoem continues to grow. Its golden shell is surprisingly solid.

name: Solgaleo
version_x: Sometimes the result of its opening an Ultra Wormhole is that energy and life-forms from other worlds are called here to this world.
version_y: In writings from the distant past, it’s called by the name “the beast that devours the sun.”

name: Lunala
version_x: Records of it exist in writings from long, long ago, where it was known by the name “the beast that calls the moon.”
version_y: It sometimes summons unknown powers and life-forms here to this world from holes that lead to other worlds.

name: Nihilego
version_x: A life-form from another world, it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.
version_y: It appeared in this world from an Ultra Wormhole. Nihilego appears to be a parasite that lives by feeding on people and Pokémon.

name: Buzzwole
version_x: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
version_y: Buzzwole goes around showing off its abnormally swollen muscles. It is one kind of Ultra Beast.

name: Pheromosa
version_x: A life-form that lives in another world, its body is thin and supple, but it also possesses great power.
version_y: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Xurkitree
version_x: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
version_y: They’ve been dubbed Ultra Beasts. Some of them stand unmoving, like trees, with their arms and legs stuck into the ground.

name: Celesteela
version_x: One of the dangerous UBs, high energy readings can be detected coming from both of its huge arms.
version_y: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Kartana
version_x: This Ultra Beast’s body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.
version_y: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Guzzlord
version_x: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
version_y: An unknown life-form called a UB. It may be constantly hungry—it is certainly always devouring something.

name: Necrozma
version_x: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It’s apparently from another world.
version_y: Light is the source of its energy. If it isn’t devouring light, impurities build up in it and on it, and Necrozma darkens and stops moving.

name: Magearna
version_x: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.
version_y: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

name: Marshadow
version_x: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it’s imitating.
version_y: It sinks into the shadows of people and Pokémon, where it can understand their feelings and copy their capabilities.

name: Poipole
version_x: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.
version_y: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.

name: Naganadel
version_x: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.
version_y: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing, venomous liquid from its needles. This liquid is also immensely adhesive.

name: Stakataka
version_x: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.
version_y: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute’s true identity was this mysterious life-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.

name: Blacephalon
version_x: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.
version_y: A UB that appeared from an Ultra Wormhole, it causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents’ surprise to rob them of their vitality.

name: Zeraora
version_x: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.
version_y: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.

name: Meltan
version_x: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.
version_y: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

name: Melmetal
version_x: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.
version_y: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal’s heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokémon.

name: Grookey
version_x: The stick Grookey holds has grown harder and more flexible after soaking in the energy that emanates from inside Grookey’s body.
version_y: As Grookey strikes everything in sight with its stick, it has more and more fun, and its rhythm becomes livelier.

name: Thwackey
version_x: It skillfully uses its two sticks not only for drumming out rapid beats but also for pummeling opponents during battle.
version_y: It becomes intensely focused while it drums out vigorous beats—so much so that sometimes it won’t listen to its Trainer’s commands.

name: Rillaboom
version_x: Though it has a calm disposition, it won’t tolerate those who drum up discord. It strictly disciplines offenders until they learn their lesson.
version_y: When one Rillaboom challenges another who leads a troop, a drumming battle commences. The victor becomes the troop’s new boss.

name: Scorbunny
version_x: Once its body has heated up, Scorbunny can use the full extent of its power. That’s why it does warm-up exercises.
version_y: Fire energy gathers in the pads of its feet, raising their temperature. Once hot, Scorbunny’s footpads can deal heavy damage to opponents.

name: Raboot
version_x: Thanks to its soft and fluffy fur, Raboot can easily heat up its fire energy and produce flames with more power.
version_y: While it prides itself on its varied kicking moves, it can also deliver powerful headbutts once its flames have heated up its forehead.

name: Cinderace
version_x: Although Cinderace loses its cool easily, it will battle flawlessly for a Trainer it trusts.
version_y: Using a ball that it made out of flames, Cinderace blinds its opponents and keeps them at bay.

name: Sobble
version_x: It gets berries to eat by shooting them down with bullets of water it spurts from its mouth. Its aim is perfect.
version_y: It’s a very cautious Pokémon. When it has no choice but to battle, it hides itself before attacking.

name: Drizzile
version_x: It extends its long, slimy tongue at blinding speeds and finishes off its prey with great skill.
version_y: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it defends its home by laying traps.

name: Inteleon
version_x: It uses special lenses in its eyes to sense things about its opponents—like their body heat—then attacks once it identifies a weak spot.
version_y: It may present itself as being well-mannered, but deep down, it still has a lazy side. It will slack off when its Trainer isn’t looking.

name: Skwovet
version_x: It stores berries in its cheeks. When there are no berries to be found, Skwovet will stuff pebbles into its cheeks to stave off its cravings.
version_y: No matter how much it stuffs its belly with food, it is always anxious about getting hungry again. So, it stashes berries in its cheeks and tail.

name: Greedent
version_x: If it spots a berry tree, it will immediately go to gather berries without a sideways glance—even if it’s in the middle of a battle.
version_y: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.

name: Rookidee
version_x: This Pokémon is brave and reckless. The white markings around a Rookidee’s eyes intimidate fainthearted Pokémon.
version_y: The females are fussier than the males. If another creature dirties a female Rookidee’s wings, it’ll peck the offender relentlessly in a burning rage.

name: Corvisquire
version_x: It’s said that the reason behind Corvisquire’s high level of intelligence is the large size of its brain relative to those of other bird Pokémon.
version_y: This intelligent Pokémon will quickly learn how to use any tool it can hold in its beak or its talons.

name: Corviknight
version_x: Corviknight can’t serve as a taxi service in Paldea because the Pokémon’s natural predators will attack it while it flies, endangering the customer.
version_y: Although its wings have partly turned to steel and become heavy as a result, this Pokémon flies through the skies with ease.

name: Blipbug
version_x: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn’t.
version_y: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

name: Dottler
weakness: Fire, Flying, Bug, Rock, Ghost, Dark
version_x: It barely moves, but it’s still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.
version_y: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

name: Orbeetle
weakness: Fire, Flying, Bug, Rock, Ghost, Dark
version_x: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.
version_y: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what’s around it—and what’s around it can include things over six miles away.

name: Nickit
version_x: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.
version_y: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.

name: Thievul
version_x: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.
version_y: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.

name: Gossifleur
version_x: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.
version_y: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

name: Eldegoss
version_x: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.
version_y: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.

name: Wooloo
version_x: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.
version_y: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won’t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

name: Dubwool
version_x: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.
version_y: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

name: Chewtle
version_x: Its large front tooth is still growing in. When the tooth itches, this Pokémon will bite another Chewtle’s horn, and the two Pokémon will tussle.
version_y: A popular game among children is to lift up sticks that Chewtle have bitten onto to see whose Chewtle can hang on the longest.

name: Drednaw
version_x: Its massive, jagged teeth can crush a boulder in a single bite. This Pokémon has an extremely vicious disposition.
version_y: Drednaw lurks along the shoreline. When prey come to drink water, Drednaw stretches its neck out and chomps down on them.

name: Yamper
version_x: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.
version_y: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

name: Boltund
version_x: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.
version_y: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.

name: Rolycoly
version_x: On sunny days, Rolycoly will come out onto grassy plains and roll around. Then it will eat the grass that gets tangled in its wheel-like leg.
version_y: Chunks of the surface of this Pokémon’s body that have grown old and flaked off have long been used for fuel as an alternative to coal.

name: Carkol
version_x: The temperature inside its body increases when it experiences strong emotions. It rolls around frantically while spewing flames.
version_y: Due to the coal tar created inside it, the heap of coal on Carkol’s back never falls apart, even when the Pokémon rolls around at high speeds.

name: Coalossal
version_x: To intimidate its opponents, Coalossal will vigorously shake its body, scattering coal from its smoldering back.
version_y: It’s gentle usually but fearsome when angered. With a body that burns at over 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit, it crushes foes and turns them to ash.

name: Applin
weakness: Ice, , Poison, Flying, Bug, Dragon, Fairy
version_x: It grows by eating the flesh of an apple. Applin uses its own body fluid to strengthen the apple’s skin and prevent it from rotting.
version_y: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.

name: Flapple
weakness: Ice, , Poison, Flying, Bug, Dragon, Fairy
version_x: It flutters around while seeking an opening in the opponent’s guard, then attacks by spitting acidic liquid strong enough to melt metal.
version_y: It uses its own body fluid to repair its apple. Strong Flapple that have won many battles have apples that are clay colored all over.

name: Appletun
weakness: Ice, , Poison, Flying, Bug, Dragon, Fairy
version_x: It feeds mainly on sweet apples. It will also eat small bug Pokémon that are attracted by its sweet nectar.
version_y: When some Lechonk come along to lick the sweet nectar on Appletun’s back, Appletun will spew sticky nectar at them to drive them away.

name: Silicobra
version_x: Silicobra’s neck pouch, which can inflate and deflate like a balloon, gets more elastic each time Silicobra sheds its skin.
version_y: Silicobra’s large nostrils are specialized for spraying sand, so this Pokémon is not very good at telling apart different smells.

name: Sandaconda
version_x: It will expand its body as much as it can and then contract itself, blasting out sand with enough force to wash away a dump truck.
version_y: The sand it spews contains sharp, pointy gravel, which is actually just sand that Sandaconda’s saliva has hardened into irregular shapes.

name: Cramorant
version_x: Cramorant instinctively swallow everything whole. They’re at their most formidable when they’re struggling to swallow overly large prey.
version_y: It’s an incredibly poor learner because it uses the bare minimum amount of energy for its brain. It focuses on battling instead.

name: Arrokuda
version_x: Arrokuda can swim quickly only in a straight line. The ones that become sluggish from overeating are the first to be targeted by flocks of Wattrel.
version_y: It takes down prey by charging into them with its hard, pointed jaw. But Arrokuda’s eyesight is poor, so this tactic has a low success rate.

name: Barraskewda
version_x: It spins its tail fins to leap from the water, then viciously bites down on Wingull flying close to the water’s surface.
version_y: It swims at speeds of over 100 knots and battles fiercely with pods of Finizen over prey.

name: Toxel
version_x: It has no problem drinking dirty water. An organ inside Toxel’s body filters such water into a poisonous liquid that is harmless to Toxel.
version_y: This selfish, attention-seeking Pokémon stores poison and electricity in two different sacs inside its body.

name: Toxtricity
version_x: Many youths admire the way this Pokémon listlessly picks fights and keeps its cool no matter what opponent it faces.
version_y: As it gulps down stagnant water and generates electricity in its body, a sound like a rhythm played by a bass guitar reverberates all around.

name: Sizzlipede
version_x: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.
version_y: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.

name: Centiskorch
version_x: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.
version_y: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

name: Clobbopus
version_x: It’s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.
version_y: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn’t alarmed when that happens—it knows they’ll grow back. It’s about as smart as a three-year-old.

name: Grapploct
version_x: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.
version_y: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.

name: Sinistea
version_x: The soul of someone who died alone possessed some leftover tea. This Pokémon appears in hotels and houses.
version_y: Sinistea gets into your body when you drink it, and then it steals your vitality from within. It also tastes awful.

name: Polteageist
version_x: The tea that composes Polteageist’s body has a distinct and enjoyable flavor. Drinking too much, however, can be fatal.
version_y: These Pokémon multiply by creeping into teapots and pouring themselves into leftover tea.

name: Hatenna
version_x: Because the emotions of others constantly flow into its head, this Pokémon prefers environments where no other creatures live.
version_y: It senses the feelings of other living creatures. Be careful not to expose it to strong emotions for too long, or it will end up exhausted.

name: Hattrem
version_x: To this Pokémon, strong emotions apparently feel like incredibly loud noises—even if the emotions are happy ones.
version_y: The moment this Pokémon finds someone who’s emitting strong emotions, it will pummel them senseless with its braids to silence them.

name: Hatterene
version_x: Hatterene knocks out those that intrude in its home forest by blasting them with a beam, then slashing with claws enhanced by psychic power.
version_y: Beware of forests that show no signs of living creatures within. You may have wandered into Hatterene’s territory.

name: Impidimp
version_x: The reason this Pokémon causes trouble for those it feels close to is because Impidimp itself gets irritable if it can’t absorb negative emotions.
version_y: They live in groups, pestering and playing pranks on each other to polish their troublemaking skills.

name: Morgrem
version_x: Morgrem prefers dirty tactics, like ambushing, because it doesn’t have confidence in its brawn.
version_y: This Pokémon absorbs negative emotions and turns them into energy. It’s popular with people who tend to think gloomy thoughts.

name: Grimmsnarl
version_x: This Pokémon has complete control over its hair. Grimmsnarl normally keeps its hair wrapped around its body to support its muscles.
version_y: It lives deep within the forest. Even after evolving into this splendid form, it hasn’t given up on its petty misdeeds and pranks.

name: Obstagoon
version_x: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.
version_y: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.

name: Perrserker
version_x: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.
version_y: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.

name: Cursola
version_x: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon’s core spirit.
version_y: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You’ll become stiff as stone if you touch it.

name: Sirfetch’d
version_x: Only Farfetch’d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon’s leek withers, it will retire from combat.
version_y: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.

name: Mr. Rime
weakness: Fire, Bug, Rock, Ghost, Dark, Steel
version_x: It’s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.
version_y: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.

name: Runerigus
version_x: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.
version_y: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you’ll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.

name: Milcery
version_x: The more sweet aromas it absorbs, the more its body swells. Milcery will deflate when its energy level drops.
version_y: When attacked, it tackles its foe and covers them in cream. With its foe either blinded or astonished by deliciousness, Milcery flees.

name: Alcremie
version_x: Desserts that Alcremie have decorated with their cream have a rich, sweet flavor and bring happiness to all who eat them.
version_y: Alcremie that have been cherished produce exquisite cream, so Trainers always raise them lovingly.

name: Falinks
version_x: The brass, which is the one that stands at the front and issues orders, is the strongest and smartest of the six.
version_y: The leader, known as the brass, uses its extendible horn to issue orders to the others when it’s time to change formation.

name: Pincurchin
version_x: This Pokémon generates electricity when it digests food. It uses its five hard teeth to scrape seaweed off surfaces and eat it.
version_y: This Pokémon is so timid that even brushing against seaweed will make it discharge electricity in surprise. Its lips do not conduct electricity.

name: Snom
version_x: It eats snow that has accumulated on the ground. It prefers soft, freshly fallen snow, so it will eat its way up a mountain, aiming for the peak.
version_y: Within its internal organs, Snom amplifies the frigid air it gets from eating snow and then uses this amplified air to create icicle-like spikes.

name: Frosmoth
version_x: Frosmoth senses air currents with its antennae. It sends its scales drifting on frigid air, making them fall like snow.
version_y: It causes blizzards as it flies around with its huge, chill-emanating wings. Clean meltwater is its favorite thing to drink.

name: Stonjourner
version_x: The elemental composition of the rocks that form its body were found to match the bedrock of a land far away from this Pokémon’s habitat.
version_y: This Pokémon spends its life gazing at the setting sun. It strides leisurely across grassy plains on legs of rock that weigh over 400 pounds each.

name: Eiscue
version_x: On hot days, these Pokémon press their ice cube heads together and pass the time cooling each other down.
version_y: If you lick the ice covering its face, you’ll find it has a faintly salty taste. This species rode here on ocean currents from a cold, faraway land.

name: Indeedee
version_x: This Pokémon picks up on the positive emotions of other creatures via its horns and uses those emotions to fuel itself.
version_y: This Pokémon never leaves its Trainer’s side. It predicts their actions with its psychic power and takes care of their day-to-day needs.

name: Morpeko
version_x: Morpeko eats seeds constantly to keep its hunger at bay. If it’s hungry for too long, it grows wild and brutish.
version_y: It has a small stomach. If it isn’t constantly eating the seeds it keeps in its pockets, it will get hungry immediately.

name: Cufant
version_x: Using the pointy tip of its trunk, it carves off chunks of hard rocks to eat. It is very docile and helps people with physical labor.
version_y: Cufant can lift loads weighing five tons. In the mornings, it heads into caves with its herd, in search of the ore on which these Pokémon feed.

name: Copperajah
version_x: This Pokémon was brought to Paldea long ago by people from a faraway land. It’s so strong that it can easily pull an airplane.
version_y: Copperajah are prideful, cantankerous Pokémon. Specimens with vibrant green skin command the respect of others of their kind.

name: Dracozolt
version_x: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.
version_y: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body, its upper half is entirely too small.

name: Arctozolt
version_x: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.
version_y: This Pokémon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.

name: Dracovish
version_x: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.
version_y: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can’t breathe unless it’s underwater.

name: Arctovish
version_x: Though it’s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.
version_y: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.

name: Duraludon
